title: louisiana pecan waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks into milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add dry ingredients to milk and eggs.
Mix thoroughly to remove lumps.
Add melted butter and blend well. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in pecans and add egg whites to batter.
Heat waffle iron.
Pour enough batter to make proper sized waffle.
Bake until iron stops steaming and waffle is golden brown.
Yields 12 small or 6 large waffles.

title: deanna's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan; set aside.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add sugar, eggs, oil and buttermilk; stir to blend.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Add strawberries and stir until thawed. Add pineapple and bananas. Pour half the mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Chill until firm. Spread half
the topping over gelatin. Pour remaining gelatin over topping. Chill. Top with remaining topping.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Combine with syrup and juice. Add rest in any order.
Let stand 30 minutes.
(I never had that much time.)
Form into 1-inch balls (or whatever size you wish). Roll in granulated sugar.

title: scripture cake
directions: I
found this; have no idea where it came from.
Wanted to share it with others.
It does make a good cake.

title: breakfast cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat milk until bubbly around the edges. Add sugar, salt and oleo to the milk.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast in water and dissolve.
Add milk mixture to yeast. add beaten eggs; then add 2 cups of flour.
Mix until smooth.
Gradually add the rest of the flour.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover top with oil or Pam.
Keep in a warm place and let rise for one hour.
Punch down and placed on a floured board and roll out.
Cover with melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up like a jelly roll and slice off.
In baking pans melt margarine and place that side up.
Allow to rose 45 minutes to one hour.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Rising time depends on thickness of dough.
They can be frosted with powdered sugar, margarine and milk icing.
Top while they are still warm.

title: chinese noodle candy
directions: Melt chips.
Add everything else.
Drop in chunks on wax paper.

title: tuna melts
directions: Mix tuna, onion, celery, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add enough Miracle Whip to hold together like tuna salad.
Butter hamburger buns on insides.
Fill buns with tuna mixture and wrap in foil. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix pudding and spread in pie shell.
Chill until set.
Spread cherry pie filling on pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: grilled three cheese potatoes
directions: Divide the potatoes and onions equally between two pieces of heavy-duty foil that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray.

title: oreo pie
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy. Add salt, baking powder and sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in crushed cookies and nuts. Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: tasty roast
directions: Mix together and pour over roast. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: king van lines cake
directions: Mix the following: cake mix, pudding, water and salad oil. Add one at a time.
Beat 6 minutes at high speed.
Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan for 40 to 45 minutes.
When done, punch holes in cake. Pour glaze over while still hot.

title: peanut butter haystacks(microwave recipe)
directions: Microwave butterscotch pieces and peanut butter on 50% power until almost melted, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Mix in nuts and chow mein noodles; drop onto wax paper by spoon.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: In a large casserole dish (8 X 14), crush 2 dozen wafers, to cover bottom of dish.
Line edges of dish with wafers, standing up.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together.
Shape into marble-sized balls.
Roll in coconut or finely chopped nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Recipe may be doubled easily.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients 3 times (with the exception of the cinnamon); cut in the shortening and add the egg and milk, which have been mixed together.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a well-greased oblong pan and cover with apples which are sliced. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes.

title: mock fish
directions: Boil 4 1/2 cups water.
In a bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Stir into cold water.
Mix well. Immediately stir the cold batter into the boiling water. Bring to a boil again.
Lower heat to simmer and cook until thickened.
Add a drained can of salmon that has been crumbled.
Pour the mush mixture into a 9 x 5-inch pan. Cover with wax paper.
Chill until next day. Slice thin and fry.

title: mrs. ferron's lemon pie
directions: Boil sugar, lemon juice and rinds for 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch and boil for 3 more minutes.
Beat yolks and add to mixture.
Turn out into precooked 9-inch pie shell and bake until pie is done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: icebox gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and molasses. Add soda and buttermilk alternately with flour.
Add spices.
Store in refrigerator until needed.
Makes 6 dozen small muffins.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: swiss mocha cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in sour cream.
Measure 1/4 cup of mixture; set remaining aside. Stir in coffee and milk into 1/4 cup of mixture.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon of Mocha flavored cheese cake mixture onto crust.
Fold Cool Whip into reserved cream cheese.
Spoon onto crust.
Drizzle with remaining mocha flavored cheese mixture.
Draw a knife or spatula through mixture to form a pattern on top.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy iron pan.
Cook to a boil past the sticky stage.
Cook until you can almost smell a burning smell. Pour onto cookie sheet and separate with a fork.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and let stand a while before cooking.
Drop by a teaspoon into hot oil.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions, peppers and garlic powder together until done (about 2 hours).
Run through sieve and then add sugar, salt, celery seed, margarine and flour.
Cook until thick.
Seal in clean hot jars.
Makes 9 to 12 pints.

title: not so sweet pecan pieroswell, new mexico
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hour or until center is firm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place cream cheese on plate; make well in center.
Mix cocktail sauce and shrimp.
Place in well of cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Mix with as little flour as possible, about 4 scant cups, sifted.
The less flour, the softer the cookies.
Chill in refrigerator a few hours or overnight.
Then roll and bake in quick oven.
Try a sample cookie before adding all the flour.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to egg mixture.
Stir in dates and nuts. Spread into 8 x 8 x 2-inch oiled pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into small bars; roll in powdered sugar.

title: batter dip for chicken or fish
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended in a small bowl.
Dip chicken or fish chunks into batter.
Drain off excess.
Deep fry until brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: apple crumb pudding
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Butter the baking dish.
Add apples and water.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, flour and butter until crumbly. Spread over apples.
Bake 60 minutes at 375°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar; cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Bake at 450°.
Can keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: great party taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix (follow package directions).
You may add some jalapeno juice while simmering to make it hotter.
Spread cream cheese on small cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Layer with ground beef, salsa, 1/3 of the cheese, lettuce, remaining cheese, tomato, jalapeno peppers and black olives.
Scoop up with tortilla chips and enjoy.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and milk. Mix sugar and cornstarch to milk and eggs. Cook until thick. Add the lemon flavoring.
Add coconut to cooked ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: pecan lush
directions: Crust:
Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Place in glass 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake 18 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp(midwest winner)
directions: In mixing bowl	combine
first	4
ingredients.
Cut in butter or margarine until	crumbly.
Press half into a greased 2 1/2 quart baking dish
or
a 9-inch square baking pan. Cover with apples.

title: jambalaya (shrimp and ham)
directions: Saute onions, peppers, garlic, celery and parsley.
Add ham, tomatoes, tomato sauce and rice.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.
Add shrimp on top and steam until shrimp turns pink (about 10 or 15 minutes).

title: curry mayonnaise
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Serve as a dip with fruit or vegetables.
Excellent with artichokes.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add margarine; mix until coarse crumbs (reserve 1 1/2 cups of this mix).
Press remaining mixture into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Combine condensed milk and peanut butter. Spread over partially baked crust to within 1/4-inch of edge. Combine reserved crumbs with M&M's.
Sprinkle over condensed milk mixture, pressing in slightly.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: doubly delicious chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt over hot water (not boiling), 1 1/2 cups chocolate morsels; cool to room temperature.
In small bowl, combine the butter, sugar and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy.
Add melted morsels and eggs; beat until light and fluffy. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 2 1/2 cups chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.
Allow to stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheets.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding, milk and Cool Whip together with a wire beater.
Layer wafers in a large bowl.
Pour pudding mixture over this and top with bananas.
Layer in this order several times. Refrigerate.

title: kidney bean stew
directions: Chop onion, dice potatoes and add kidney beans, tomatoes, cooked rice, butter, salt and pepper to suit your taste.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Water may be added if required.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients in blender and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until firm in center.

title: neiman-marcus squares
directions: Mix devil's food cake mix, butter and egg.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans and chips evenly over cake.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Spread evenly over cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake top is golden and bubbly.

title: country stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except biscuits.
Stir until well mixed and heated.
Put biscuits on top and bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: old-fashioned apple dessert
directions: Mix apples, bread crumbs, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Pour melted butter and water over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are soft.
Serve with ice cream or cream.

title: twinkie cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Whip cream, add to cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Line 10-inch spring-form pan with twinkies cut in half.
Pour filling into pan, refrigerate overnight.
Top with chilled pie filling.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make a white sauce using margarine, flour, milk and salt.
Put a layer of potatoes and sprinkle with pepper, onion, parsley and cheese.
Repeat until all potatoes are used.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake until brown.

title: no fat spinach dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese in blender or food processor until smooth.
Add Knorr soup mix and dressing.
Thaw spinach; rinse and squeeze all water out.
Add to mixture.
Cut hole in center of pumpernickel bread and use for bowl.
Use cut out bread for dipping.

title: chocolate-peppermint flip
directions: Whirl all ingredients in blender until well mixed.
Makes about 4 cups.
Enjoy!!!

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat cottage cheese until warm. Add sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda and yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition. (For first addition of flour, use mixer on low speed.)
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and double in size, 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir dough down; put in two small loaf pans (7 3/4 x 3 x 3) that have been greased well or sprayed with Pam.

title: corn-kernel cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk, margarine and corn; add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Goes well with hot soup or chile.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Chop all ingredients; mix well.
Add 2 tablespoon salt.
Wait 15 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup sugar and 1 cup vinegar.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: granny white meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup into meat balls.
Brown meat balls and drain off grease.
Add chicken soup or gravy plus 1 can of water.
Simmer one hour.

title: brownie cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In mixing bowl, beat flour, sugar, melted butter, cocoa, 2 eggs, milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla and baking powder until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spread into pan.
In smaller bowl, beat the cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, then remaining 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla, beating until smooth.
Pour over brownie batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until top is slightly brown.
Cool; refrigerate. Cut into bars.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator.

title: chicken pie(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Boil fryer; take meat off bone and pinch up.
Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour soup and broth over chicken.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over crust. Bake until brown.
May have to turn on broiler to brown on top.

title: garden chicken casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring broth and 1/3 c. sherry to a boil. Add contents of rice package, cover and simmer over low heat 25 to 30 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a Dutch Oven, saut onion, carrots, and green pepper in butter until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add rice, chicken and mushrooms, mixing well.
Place cream cheese, American cheese, and milk in a saucepan and melt over medium heat, stirring until smooth.
Add to Dutch oven with remaining sherry, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2 in. casserole dish. Top with Parmesan cheese and almonds.
Cover and bake 35 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or bubbly.
If desired, garnish with carrots and green onions.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes or until pale yellow. Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice. Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. Fold into pumpkin mix.
Pour batter into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on a towel.
Loosen edges of cake and invert on towel.
Roll cake and towel from narrow edges. Cool cake completely.
Unroll and spread with filling.
Reroll and chill.

title: frosted lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 8 x 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill.
When firm, unmold or leave in pan and frost top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and let chill.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts.

title: pita triangles with tomato dill sauce
directions: Note: To peel, seed, and chop tomatoes, plunge them into boiling water for 15-20 seconds; remove and cool. Use a sharp paring knife to peel off the skin, then cut each tomato in half horizontally. Squeeze halves to remove seeds, then chop.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Drain well. Pack pickles in jars.
Mix other ingredients and pour over pickles.
Seal and refrigerate.
Will be ready to eat in about 1 week.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in baking dish; sprinkle with orange juice.
Mix all other ingredients.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Blend green pepper, onion, and tomato sauce in blender.
Cook and drain noodles.
Slice olives.
Add everything together and bake in a 350 degree oven for one hour. (Great for freezing.)

title: basic yeast bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix to dissolve. Set aside to cool.
Dissolve yeast with warm water.
Beat egg and add to yeast mixture.
Add milk mixture and flour.
(You want dough to be stiff enough to work, but not too stiff.)
Set aside for approximately 1 hour to rise.
Note:
Leave in bowl for first rising.
After mixture has doubled in bulk, turn out on a floured surface and knead about 5 to 10 minutes, adding flour if necessary. Divide dough in half and shape into the type rolls you want.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Drain Veg-All.
Then put Veg-All and potatoes on top of chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup, chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste and cornstarch. Pour mixture over Veg-All and potatoes.
Mix together flour, milk and butter. Pour this over the top of pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour or until golden brown.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Mix sauce ingredients.
Spread bottom half of buns with soft margarine, toast lightly.
Season meat with salt and pepper and onion, mixing well.
Spread meat mixture over toasted buns.
Bake at 400° for 15 minute.
Remove from oven, top with cheese, cover with heated tops of buns and serve.

title: caramel candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt; add 1/2 cup cream.
Cook and stir until soft ball stage.
Add another 1/2 cup cream, continue to cook and stir and let it reach 236°.
Stir last 1/2 cup cream and cook and stir until the candy thermometer reaches 242°. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and nuts; let cool to 200° before pouring into buttered
9 x 9-inch dish with Handi-Wrap in the bottom.
Don't use wax paper or the caramel will stick.

title: feta cheese ball
directions: Soften all and mix well until blended.
Enjoy!

title: apple cream pie
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with two knives or a pastry cutter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with vanilla and stir in with fork.
Sprinkle with water, 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring until pastry holds together.
Shape into a ball.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Transfer to 9-inch pie plate.
Trim and flute.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place	diced
potatoes
into
a
casserole
dish.
Mix margarine, chicken soup, onion and cheese together.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake for 45 minutes. Cover with foil while baking.
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Chill and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Dust raisins and pecans with 2 tablespoons of dry mixture.
Mix dry ingredients to wet.
Fold in raisins and pecans. Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugars, shortening, eggs, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Roll about 2 teaspoons of cookie batter in hands to form a ball.
Place balls on a cookie sheet and press each one in the center firmly with a fork. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Rub salt and pepper into steaks and brown in shortening in large skillet.
Remove steaks; add onions to drippings and brown. Add mushrooms, water, bouillon and steaks.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove steaks to a platter.
Mix cornstarch with sour cream and stir into gravy.
Heat; do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper and pour over the steaks.
Serve over noodles, rice or potatoes.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Line bottom and sides of a 3-quart bowl with vanilla wafers. Slice 1 banana and layer over wafers. Spoon 1/3 of the pudding mixture over the banana.
Repeat layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding twice. Chill. Spread whipped topping over the pudding.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, or at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: peach bread
directions: Empty contents of muffin and cake mix into large bowl.
Peaches can be chopped or left in halves.
Peaches also must be drained of juice.
Combine peaches, eggs, butter and milk.
Mix all the ingredients with a cake mixer or beat with hand strokes.
Batter can be whipped or slightly thick.
Bake at 350° to 375° in a greased pan.
Baking time is approximately 30 minutes or when browning on top.
Served best after cooling at room temperature.

title: salad for dinner
directions: After boiling chicken breasts, cool and chop into squares. Be sure to remove skin.
Chop lettuce and place in a large bowl. Add sunflower seeds, cheese and raisins to lettuce.
Add carrots and chicken, then stir and serve.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cooked dressing for turkey
directions: Boil onion and celery in broth until tender.
Add margarine to broth to melt.
Mix onions, celery, and beaten egg with broth and margarine. Pour over cornbread and bread crumbs and mix.
Put in buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: celia's apricot mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sour cream and baby food.
Beat.
Fold cup of apricots into mixture and pour into mold.
This makes a beautiful tasty mold.
Sometimes I also fold a cup of pineapple chunks with it for a little different taste.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries (slightly thawed) and stir until berries are completely dissolved.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half the mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When this mixture is firm (doesn't take long), spread sour cream and remaining jello to form top layer.
Chill several hours until firm.
Serve.

title: tex-mex salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Drain and rinse with cold water until cool.
In a large bowl, blend mayonnaise and Italian dressing. Add green chiles, chili powder and cumin.
Combine cooked pasta with half of the parsley, beans, corn, tomato and green pepper. Add chopped ham and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate to chill.
Just before serving, garnish with remaining chopped parsley.
Makes 12 to 18 servings.

title: appetizer artichoke frittata
directions: Drain marinade from artichokes into a skillet.
Chop artichokes; set aside.
Add onions and garlic to skillet; saute until onions are limp.
In a bowl, beat eggs with a wire whisk. Add crackers, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese, parsley, pimentos and artichokes.
Add onion mixture.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes, until set.
Let cool in pan, then cut into bite size squares.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: block party barbecue
directions: Put the first 7 ingredients in a roaster.
Cover and bake in a 275° oven until fork-tender, about 5 to 6 hours.
Reserve 1 cup of meat juices.
Chill meat for easier slicing.
Remove excess fat from meat, slice thinly across grain.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each egg.

title: easy chocolate trifle
directions: Cook cake by directions on box; cool completely.
Cut cake into small pieces.
Prepare pudding by box directions.
Layer in order as follows three times:
cake, strawberry pie filling and Cool Whip.
Spread jello pudding on top.
Sprinkle almonds and sliced strawberries on top.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Beat lemonade in large bowl about 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon in Cool Whip, blending well.
Add condensed milk until well mixed. Pour mixture into graham cracker pie crust, smooth over.
Freeze overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Let set until slightly thickened. Add pineapple, marshmallows, 1/2 can of lemon pie filling and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Pour in square or oblong 8 x 11-inch glass dish. Let set and spread remaining pie filling over Jell-O and remaining Cool Whip on top.
Can garnish top with lemon slices, maraschino cherries or nuts.

title: joan's chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead until smooth. You may need to use more powdered sugar. Dough should be pliable but not sticky. If too sticky, chill for a short time.

title: baked onions
directions: Peel onions and cut in half.
Pour mushroom soup over onions and sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 325° to 350° until tender.

title: broccoli-corn chowder
directions: Combine chicken, 3 teaspoons of the salt and 4 cups of water in kettle.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Take meat from bones; dice.
Strain broth into a 4-cup measure. Add water, if needed, to make 4 cups.
Saute onion in butter or oleo until soft in same kettle.
Add lima beans, soups, 2 soup cans of water and celery; cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until beans are tender.
Stir in chicken, broth, corn and remaining 2 teaspoons of seasoned salt.
Heat slowly just to boiling.
Ladle into heated soup bowls.

title: no cholesterol yeast cake
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Wait a few minutes until mixture bubbles.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Mix with mixer or knead.
Mixture should not be too soft and not too hard.
Let rise approximately 1 hour.
Divide into 6 balls.
Roll out into 12 x 15-inch rectangle (approximately).
Fill with 3/4 to 1 cup sugar and 3 to 4 ounces cocoa (depending on how sweet it is desired). Roll into 15-inch logs.
Let rise 3/4 to 1 hour.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Use for a vegetable dip.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature; whip until fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk while continuing to beat until well blended. Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well. Pour into crust. Chill 2 or 3 hours before garnishing top of pie with pie filling.

title: biscuit bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter.
Spray Pam in a large metal ring mold.
Spread Parmesan on foil.
Dip biscuits in butter, then cheese.
Stand on end in mold until it is filled.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Scrape sides with spatula until bread is loosened.
Unmold, wrap in foil.
May be frozen.

title: church supper stew
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 5-quart casserole.
(If desired, brown beef cubes in hot fat.)
In casserole, layer beef, potatoes, carrots, onions and celery, sprinkling salt as you go. (Salt may be omitted if on low salt diet.) Spoon soups out of cans on top.
Pour ginger all over.
Cover.
Bake 3 hours or until beef is tender.
Uncover last 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: happy home
directions: Mix altogether.
Keeping Christ as the head, place into a safe, peaceful harbor and pray, pray, pray.

title: moist and crispy chicken
directions: Place crushed Rice Krispies cereal, paprika, salt and pepper in large plastic food bag.
Shake to blend well.
Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place one piece at a time in bag. Shake to coat well.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender.

title: noodle candy
directions: Melt chips over hot water.
Add peanut butter.
Add peanuts and noodles and remove from heat.
Stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in mixer.
Pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Mix next 5 ingredients for glaze. Can
sprinkle powdered sugar over glaze.
Can sprinkle candy over this.

title: tex-mex spice mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and store mixture in a sealed container in cool, dark, dry place up to 3 months.
Yield: 8 1/2 tablespoons.
Use in any recipe that calls for chili powder; sprinkle on meat for fajitas, tacos, etc., or any recipe that needs some zip.
Also good in taco salad.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well; shape into a loaf.
Cover with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Coat chops with flour and brown in oil in hot skillet. Combine soup with water.
Pour over the chops that have been placed in a baking dish.
Place 1/2 can of onion rings on top of chops.
Cover; bake at 350° until tender, about an hour.
Uncover; sprinkle with the rest of the onions.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: beef
directions: In a small bowl stir together flour and milk until smooth. Add butter and bring to a boil.
Sprinkle over the beef, then sprinkle cheese over it, too.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pasta fusigle
directions: In a pot, put a little oil. Add the garlic powder. When garlic powder is brown, throw in the tomatoes, salt and pepper; stir. Take the beans and put in pot; let cook 10 minutes. Cook macaroni until little tender; drain, then add to pot. If it gets a little dry, add water. Serve with grated Romano cheese.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Butter 9-inch pie plate.
Peel and slice onion into 1/4-inch rounds.
Saute in butter in saucepan until soft, not brown.
Whisk other ingredients until well mixed.

title: date sandwich cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla together. Add dry ingredients. Form into small walnut-sized balls with floury hands. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: hardanger lefse
directions: Add soda to buttermilk, then mix ingredients and add enough flour to roll out very thin to about a 12-inch size.
Bake on a griddle.
Lefse can be softened by wrapping in a wet cloth.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: In a saucepan, blend together sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and margarine.
Mix.
Bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes or 230° on candy thermometer.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla, nuts and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat well until mixture becomes very thick. Add miniature marshmallows.
Stir just enough to mix in marshmallows.
Pour in well-greased glass dish (Pam works well). Let cool and cut into squares.
Believe it or not, this fudge freezes very well in tightly closed plastic containers.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine lemonade and milk; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.

title: warm brownie pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square baking dish. Combine flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and 1/3 cup cocoa in medium bowl.
Combine milk, butter and vanilla in measuring cup; stir into dry ingredients just until blended.
Spoon batter evenly into prepared dish.
Combine brown sugar and remaining 1/4 cup cocoa in small bowl.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour boiling water over entire mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 35 to 38 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream if desired.
Makes 8 servings (235 calorie, 6 gm fat, 14 mg cholesterol).

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture along with sour cream, vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Fold in coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in tube pan.

title: potato-topped meat loaf
directions: Measure 1/4 cup from 12 ounce jar of home style brown gravy. Combine with ground beef, bread crumbs, chopped onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Form into a shallow loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and drain fat.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix all together, except pie crust.
Put in
pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Drop macaroni in 3 cups rapidly boiling salted water (2 teaspoons salt).
Bring back to rapid boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Cover with tight fitting lid, remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes.
Rinse with hot water; drain. Heat oven to 350°.
Place alternating layers of macaroni, cheese and milk in greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, until golden brown on top.
Serve with seasoned stewed tomatoes, salad and crusty bread. Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese pastry shells
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut into shortening.
Stir in cheese. Sprinkle one tablespoon water over part of the mixture; toss gently with fork.
Push aside.
Repeat, adding enough of the water so entire mix is moistened.
Form into a ball.
Roll dough into a 12 x 12-inch square on a lightly floured surface.
Cut into 36 (2 x 2-inch) squares.
Grease mini-muffin cups.
Press dough squares allowing points to stick up.
Prick with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden in color.
Remove shells from pans; cool on wire racks.
Shells may be filled with egg, tuna and/or ham salad, with a hot Sloppy Joes mix or a cold or hot mix of your choice.

title: curry chicken(spicy)
directions: Place one whole chicken (cut) on sheet pan sprayed with Pam or greased with butter.
Place in oven set at 450° for 3 hours.

title: dave's red hot bloody mary
directions: Combine V-8, spices, sauces and lemon juice in a small pitcher, stirring to blend well.
Pour gin or vodka in glasses and fill with juice.
Add one cube of ice.
Garnish with a celery stick, if desired.
Makes 3 drinks.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together cheese and chili. Microwave on Medium-high (7) for 9 to 11 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes. Stir well and let stand a few minutes before serving. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine; add graham cracker crumbs, sugar and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips; spread over top.
Chill until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then beat sugar and flour.
Add melted butter, milk and nutmeg.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake until filling is firm.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: In same dish combine ingredients.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes, uncovered; stir.
Then cook 15 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: taco dip and doritos
directions: On a serving type round dish (not too deep), put the sour cream on and add the taco seasoning.
Mix thoroughly.
Add toppings:
chopped tomatoes, lettuce, olives, onions, etc.
or only what you like.
Dip with nacho cheese Doritos.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Bake chicken and shred.

title: butter dipped biscuits
directions: Add enough milk to the flour to make it easy to drop dough from a spoon into the melted butter.
Drop and coat entire biscuit.
Place in baking pan. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into bits.
Shred Mozzarella cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Serve on fresh lettuce bed or without.

title: chocolate chip coconut cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs, shortening, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix together flour, baking soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Stir well, then add coconut and chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: potatoes with feta cheese
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until done.
Peel and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine potatoes, pimiento stuffed olives, 1 1/4 cups Feta cheese, 1/3 cup half and half, butter, white pepper and garlic salt.
Gently toss.
Spoon into greased casserole, 10 x 6 x 2-inches.
Saute pepper in 2 tablespoons butter.
Arrange around edge of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix and press into pie plate and bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden.

title: festive holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let sit in refrigerator until firm.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the steak in large saucepan.
Add onion, mushrooms, soup, water and sour cream.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Pour over cooked egg noodles.
Add 1 can French fried onions.
Bake until light golden.

title: light orange cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup orange juice in a blender. Heat remaining cup of juice to boiling and add to blender.
Cover and blend at high speed until gelatin dissolves.
Add orange rind, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, egg yolks, cottage cheese and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into large bowl; chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Beat together 1 cup sugar, flour and milk and add to melted butter.
Do not stir.
Mix fresh fruit, water and 1 cup sugar and pour in middle of mixture.
Do not stir. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: holiday ham
directions: Baste ham with brown sugar before baking.
Bake 1/2 hour for each pound.

title: date ball cookies
directions: Grease a heavy pan with butter.
Put in first 4 ingredients and cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Let cool.
Butter hands and roll into small balls (teaspoon), then roll in shredded coconut.

title: anniegal's congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add crushed pineapple and chill till thick.
Stir in sour cream and pour into mold.
Chill until set.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients in a large skillet; cover.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or longer if needed.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: Bring a pan of water to boil. Cook the tortellini until done. Add your can of alfredo sauce to paste. Serve with a salad.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken and tear into small pieces.
Mix together soups, tomatoes, water, Velveeta and English peas; heat until cheese melts.
Crush Tostitos.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Steam broccoli, cauliflower and carrots until tender.
Melt butter; add flour and salt.
Stir until blended.
Add milk; stir until thick.
Lower heat and add cheese.
Stir until melted. Place steamed vegetables in casserole dish and cover with cheese mixture.

title: party mini sandwiches
directions: Cook together hamburger, sausage, green pepper and seasonings. Drain.
Add 1 pound Velveeta cheese; heat until melted.
Put between 2 slices party rye bread.
Can be fixed ahead and frozen; then heat in microwave or oven when needed.

title: hurry-up sausage and bean soup
directions: Place beans, onion and garlic in food processor bowl fitted with steel blade or blender container; process until smooth, scraping bowl as necessary.
Add broth, sherry and cumin; process until blended.
Pour into medium saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage; cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in parsley.
Garnish with lemon and sour cream.
Makes 2 servings each with 496 calories, 23 g fat and 56 mg cholesterol.

title: breakfast biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in microwave or on top of stove.
Dip individual biscuits into melted butter on both sides and then into sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake in oven according to package directions. Works best on insulated cookie sheet.

title: cincinnati chili(served over spaghetti)
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot and bring to boil. Stir and boil until ground beef is cooked thoroughly. Lower heat. Cover and simmer for 3 or 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaves before serving. Serve over spaghetti. Top with kidney beans, chopped onions and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: creole sole
directions: Saute bell pepper, celery and onion in olive oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in fresh tomato, bay leaf, thyme, cloves, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Simmer gently 5 to 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Into large oblong greased pan, dump ingredients in order listed.
Chop up butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not stir mixture.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Combine all in large dish and then add cooked noodles. Put in casserole dish (2 qt) and baked covered for 30 minutes at 350. Uncover dish, sprinkle with cheese, and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: lemon-garlic chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients for marinade.
Marinate chicken overnight (or all day).
Cook chicken on grill, basting with marinade.

title: coffee custard
directions: Pour coffee over marshmallows.
Stir in the whipped cream. Spoon into sherbet glasses and refrigerate overnight.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Using 2 forks, roll bread strips in sweetened condensed milk, coating all sides, then roll in coconut. Place on well-greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove at once from baking sheet.
Makes about 24.

title: easy frozen yogurt
directions: In medium size bowl, mix all ingredients.
Freeze for about 4 hours; stir hourly for first 3 hours.

title: country scrabble
directions: Simmer meat in 4 cups of water for 1 hour.
Bone meat and chop fine.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar.
Slowly add package of jello.
Beat evaporated milk and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: quick carrot soup
directions: In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, melt butter.
Add carrots and onions.
Cook until onions soften, about 5 minutes. Add broth, tarragon and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until carrots are tender, about 5 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix thoroughly; roll and chill.
After chilled, roll in crushed pecans or walnuts.

title: meat pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Prick bottom and sides of pie shell with fork.
Partially bake crust on cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
In large skillet, brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain well.
Add green pepper, mushroom and onion.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in water, spaghetti sauce, basil and garlic powder and simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle half of Parmesan over bottom of crust.
Spread half of meat mixture over Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella cheese over meat.
Layer remaining meat and Parmesan cheese.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 minutes.
Sprinkle top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats and brown sugar.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts. Pat mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes. Stir while still warm to crumble; cool.

title: easy biscuit sweet roll dough
directions: Stir to dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix together sugar, salt, dry milk, eggs, butter or shortening and 1 1/2 cups water. Stir in yeast mixture.
Beat in 3 cups sifted flour.
Beat well. Add 4 2/3 cups sifted flour and knead on lightly floured board. Place in greased bowl and grease up side.
Cover and allow to double in bulk.

title: meat sauce for roasts(gives a delicious added flavor)
directions: Put all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Best served with lamb, but also good with any other kind of meat.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco, sugar, baking powder and 5 eggs.
Add flour and milk slowly.
Add flavorings last.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° or 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit well and place in casserole.
Melt butter, sugar, cinnamon and curry powder and pour over fruit.
Bake in a 325° oven for at least 30 minutes.
Keep hot and serve from the chafing dish. I have used other fruit combinations.

title: baked chicken breasts #2
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Coat breasts with mixture.
Roll in stuffing crumbs.
Place in buttered baking dish and dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange icing
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook 3 minutes or until thick. Spread on while cake is warm.
Ample icing for a 2 layer cake.

title: venison chili
directions: Cook bacon in Dutch oven until crisp.
Remove bacon with slotted spoon, reserving drippings into Dutch oven.
Set bacon aside.
Add venison and onion to Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat until meat is brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain off pan drippings; add bacon, water and next 6 ingredients and bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans.
Cover and cook 30 minutes more. Serve with sour cream, green onions and cheese, if desired.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni with 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix salad ingredients with the mayonnaise, salt, A.1. sauce and mustard.
Mix well.
Cover and serve warm or cold with cheesy crackers.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add
eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add crushed bananas
and
nuts.
Blend in well.
Add flour, sifted with baking soda
and
salt.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
One
loaf
pan serves 4 to 6 people.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, toss first 6 ingredients.
Toss lightly until well blended.
Shape into bite-sized meatballs.
Roll in flour.
Preheat pan to 320° or medium-hot.
Add oil.
Add floured meatballs to oil and brown on all sides.
Remove meatballs to paper towel as they brown.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well to bring up bits of browned meat from bottom of pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add meatballs to sauce.
Cover and simmer gently 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve as hot appetizers with toothpicks.
Makes 50.

title: punch
directions: Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves about 40 (1/2 cup each).

title: microwave flo's quiche
directions: Spread cheese over bottom of pie shell.
Mix together milk, eggs, pepper and salt.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle onion rings over top.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes until center is firm.
Let rest 5 minutes.
(Use 50% power and cook 12 to 14 minutes.)

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease tube or Bundt pan.
Beat eggs in bowl; add sugar and beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to batter with oil, vanilla and orange juice.
Prepare 5 cups peeled apples, cut or sliced into small pieces.
Mix with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Put 1/2 batter in greased pan; spread 1/2 of the apples on top.
Add remaining batter and then the balance of the apples to topping.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: no-fry doughnuts
directions: In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour. Blend 1/2 minute on low, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes at medium, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth, scraping side of bowl.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.

title: carrot salad
directions: Empty carrots in bowl.
Add all the other ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in loaf pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta with escarole and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Wash escarole thoroughly in cold water several times; drain in colander.
In a large skillet, add oil and garlic.
While cooking pasta, heat oil and garlic in skillet, then saute cut up escarole, sun-dried tomatoes, salt, pepper and dash of hot pepper flakes. Do not overcook.
Before draining pasta, add some of that water to skillet.
Drain pasta; pour escarole mixture over pasta.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and pepper in 3 tablespoons fat.
Add ground beef and cook until it falls apart.
Stir in tomatoes, rice or noodles, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, removing cover last 15 minutes.

title: jeanette's pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pumpkin mixture.
Melt and drizzle melted butter over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Top with Dream Whip.
Serves approximately 15 large servings.

title: swiss chicken breast
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and top with cheese.
Stir milk and
soup
until
smooth; our over chicken. Toss croutons in butter;
sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is cooked.

title: oat and rice burgers(makes 10 patties)
directions: Mix together all ingredients and form into patties.
Spray lightly the baking pan with Pam or spread thin coat of olive oil on pan.
Place patties into pan and bake at 325° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Leftovers can be frozen and used later.

title: mexican chicken burgers
directions: Combine chicken, bread crumbs and milk in bowl.
Stir in onions, cilantro, cumin, salt and pepper.
Place remaining bread crumbs in pie plate.
With slightly wet hands, shape mixture into patties.
Coat with crumbs.
Heat oil in skillet on medium heat. Cook until meat is no longer pink.

title: festive fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with Eagle Brand and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts, if desired, and vanilla. Spread evenly onto wax paper or buttered foil-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Other great fudge flavors:

title: easy fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan combine first four ingredients.
Bring to boiling over medium heat; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and immediately add chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl; blend well.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend; do not beat.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain off fat.
In a saucepan, melt the 1/4 cup butter or margarine.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in cooked sausage, sliced eggs, green pepper and drained corn.

title: whooping cough syrup
directions: Put flax seed in a bag; pour over it 1 1/2 pints of water. Let simmer down to 1/2 that amount.
Remove from fire and add other ingredients while still hot.

title: baby back ribs with squash and beans
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, cut racks of ribs into 2 rib portions.
In 10-inch skillet over high heat, heat ribs and enough water to cover to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut acorn squash into 3/4-inch wedges.

title: chuck's spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 2 hours. Serve in a hollowed out Hawaiian bread loaf, cutting hollowed out part into bite-sized pieces for dipping.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and flour with buttermilk.
Mix well with electric beater until creamy, then add eggs.
Beat well, adding flavoring.
Bake in a stem pan or a sheet cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 5 minutes; turn out on a cake dish.

title: meat loaf and roasted potatoes
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef or turkey, 1/2 can onions, egg and Worcestershire sauce thoroughly.
In baking pan, shape firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Place potatoes around meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir potatoes.

title: crunchy apple crisp(microwave)
directions: Spread apple slices in 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) glass baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients, except oleo, in a medium bowl. Cut in oleo until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Microwave for 12 to 16 minutes on High.

title: candied nuts
directions: Bring brown sugar and milk to soft boil stage, 240°.
Add vanilla and butter;
take off heat.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour onto buttered tinfoil and separate them.
Dry overnight.

title: chicken stuffed crescent
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients (except rolls) together and then spoon into the 8 crescent triangles.
Roll up and seal completely.
(Optional: dip tops in melted butter, then dip in mixture of crushed bread stuffing and finely chopped nuts.) Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.
May serve with chicken gravy; packaged kind is fine.

title: do-nuts
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart pan, combine sugar, salt, butter and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add all flour.
Beat until flour is moistened.
Cook over medium heat, beating vigorously until dough forms a ball.
Remove from heat and add eggs, one at a time, beating with mixer.
Batter should be smooth and shiny.
Add vanilla.
Drop rounded tablespoons in hot oil.
Coat with powdered sugar.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Roll into balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hobnail icing
directions: Place bowl in ice water.
Use mixer to beat until of spreading consistency.
Spread icing smoothly on cake.

title: lemon fluff cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together in a bowl. Make a well; add oil, egg yolks, water, lemon juice and rind. Beat until smooth.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat very, very stiff.
Blend gently with cake mix.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 80 minutes.
Remove when cool.

title: pepper hash
directions: Grind peppers and onions, add salt and let stand for 10 min. Pour boiling water over, rinse and drain as well as possible. Pour on sugar and vinegar, let come to a boil and cook for 10 min. Seal in hot sterilzed jars.

title: texas earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in 9 x 13-inch cake pan (sprayed with Pam).
Mix cake according to directions on the box.
Pour it over the coconut and pecans.
Cream margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls all over unbaked cake.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick and pulls away from sides.
Add rice cereal and chopped nuts.
Make into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, soda, Karo and butter.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball stage.
Add pecans; beat until thick and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into small florets; wash and drain.
Mix ingredients with large bottle of creamy bacon salad dressing; chill.
Before serving, sprinkle dried dill weed on top.

title: date nut fingers
directions: Cook the first five ingredients for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until mixed. Cool only until the mixture can be handled.
Shape into fingers, roll in coconut and finish cooling.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse chicken pieces with water and pat dry with paper towels.
In a small, microwave-proof bowl, melt butter or margarine.
Add seasonings.
Set aside.

title: patty's wheat germ muffins
directions: Mix egg, sugar, milk and melted butter; sift flour, salt and baking powder and add to egg mixture. Fold in wheat germ. Bake in greased muffin tins 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 18.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix in large glass bowl the sugar and corn syrup; cook on High for 5 minutes in microwave.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups dry roasted peanuts.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until brown.
Add vanilla, butter and soda; mix until foamy and spread on cookie sheet until cool, then break up.

title: cookbook quickies
directions: Cut out centers of Cookbook Brown 'N Serve rolls.
Fill with mixture of chicken or tuna salad.
Place in hot oven at 375° until golden brown.
Serve with punch.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix Karo syrup, sugar and eggs in top of double boiler and heat until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: In a blender, mix all ingredients until thick and smooth. Serve immediately in tall glass.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Place the marshmallows, Pet milk and sugar in a double boiler. Stir until marshmallows melt.
Cool and pour over the remaining ingredients, then mix well.
Place in mold or back in cracker box.
Let set for 5 days in refrigerator.

title: cheese-onion pie(a big favorite, precursor of quiche)
directions: Mix crushed crackers with 1/4 pound melted butter or margarine.
Press into a buttered 9-inch pie tin, to form the crust.
(Any baking dish will do.)

title: sugar tarte
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine butter and flour.
Mix well.
Add the brown sugar and hot milk.
Mix well.
Cook mixture on medium heat and stir until thickened.
Pour into a prepared pie crust. Can be decorated with meringue or whipped cream.
Let cool.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; rub with oil and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour. Pierce in several places and continue baking for about 1/2 hour or until very tender.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Cut off a large oval piece from long side of each potato, and with a small spoon, gently scrape out cooked potato, leaving skin intact.
Place potato in medium bowl with milk and egg and beat until very smooth. Set aside.
In butter, cook onion and garlic until tender.
Add to potatoes, along with remaining ingredients and stir thoroughly. Fill each potato skin until heaping.
Bake in oven on tray for about 15 minutes, just until tops begin to brown.
Serve hot.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Cut in oleo, cheese with flour and seasonings.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
It will be stiff.
Form into balls and put on greased baking sheet.
Press balls down with fork.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.
This has a very unusually crispy texture.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Place chocolate bits, oleo, salt and water in saucepan over low heat until melted; add vanilla.
In large bowl, place sugar; pour in chocolate mixture, mixing very well until smooth and glossy.
Add nuts.
Butter pan and press in fudge (8-inch square pan).
Cool until set in fridge.
Makes 60 pieces.

title: chocolate caramel chew(excellent for holidays and parties)
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan.
Sprinkle nuts across bottom of pan.
Mix brown sugar and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir constantly over medium heat for 7 minutes.
Remove and pour over nuts.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel mixture.
Cover with foil.
Wait 5 minutes.
Remove foil. Spread melted chips across caramel mixture evenly.
Cut into pieces.
Put into refrigerator for 1 hour.
Then eat and Enjoy! (Tastes like Heath bars.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for 15 minutes and drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetables mix on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add water, chicken cubes, salt, garlic powder and broccoli.
Cook until tender, then add noodles.
Cook until tender.
Add milk and cheese and cook until cheese is melted; don't boil (simmer).

title: old fashioned vinegar roll
directions: Roll pastry 1/8-inch thick.
Spread with butter and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Roll as jelly roll; cut into 1-inch slices and place in baking dish.
Mix vinegar and water; pour over slices. Sprinkle with remainder of sugar and nutmeg. Dot with remaining butter. Bake at 400° until brown, but not dry.
Serve warm.

title: mildred's kidney bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Tastes best if allowed to set 24 hours.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches). Mix all ingredients, spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces, about 2 x 1-inch.
Makes about 4 dozen appetizers.

title: no sugar apple bran muffins
directions: Saute apples in margarine 10 minutes or until tender.
Pour boiling water over bran.
Add apples, buttermilk, eggs, blackstrap molasses and dates.
Combine flour, baking soda and spices; stir into bran mixture just until combined.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container at least 24 hours.
You can keep in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Fill greased muffin pan 3/4 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Combine first four ingredients in bowl, beating well.
Beat in milk gradually.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into punch bowl and garnish with sprinkle of nutmeg.
Yields 16 servings.
Has 225 calories per serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into casserole and put Ritz cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften and mix cream cheese and margarine; stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend until smooth.
Stir in cake flour.
Blend mixture until doughy texture.
If desired, add chopped nuts.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir bacon in last.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix dry milk and water; set in a pan of very hot hot.
Add sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Equal to 1 can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: pineapple-orange punch
directions: Combine sugar with just enough water to dissolve.
Heat to make a

title: turkey salad
directions: Put turkey into a large bowl with celery, nuts, peas, onions, salt and lemon pepper marinade and toss lightly to mix.
Add mayonnaise; toss gently to coat evenly.
Chill.
Spoon into crisp lettuce cups and garnish with walnut halves.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat soup and stir into gelatin.
Cream cheese with a little milk until smooth.
Stir into soup-gelatin mixture.
Add other ingredients; blend well. Pour into a 2-quart mold and refrigerate until set.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients to your taste.
Add a squirt of lemon if desired.
Salt and pepper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, remove from bone and chop into bite size pieces. Grease bottom of casserole dish and place one pie crust in the bottom of dish.
Put chicken on top of crust.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Place second pie crust on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: new england dip
directions: Blend all ingredients, chill and serve with crackers or chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pasta bella
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large saute skillet.
Add garlic and vegetables, except for broccoli and tomatoes.
Saute on medium heat until tender.
Add tomatoes and saute until tender.
Drain off 1/2 the butter and return skillet to low heat.
Cook and drain pasta while sauteing vegetables.
Add pasta to vegetables; add Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Continue tossing until cheese is melted.

title: fat free chocolate cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Then, add Karo syrup and egg whites, mixing by hand.
Drop rounded spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
While cooling, sprinkle with 10x sugar. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk; blend well.
Add diced peaches to melted butter in pan.
Pour mixture batter over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 8.

title: mussels in herb butter(for 5 to 6 servings)
directions: Place mussels under running water for at least 30 minutes, then clean by scrubbing with a brush.
Remove dark, hairy beard. Place them in a pot with the wine; cover and set over medium-high heat.
When it comes to a boil, lower the heat and shake the covered pot occasionally.
When mussels open, remove immediately from the heat.
In another pan, melt butter and saute garlic.
Add parsley, bread crumbs and soy sauce and stir together.
Discard the empty half of the shell and place mussels (in remaining half shells) in a baking pan.
Spoon 1 teaspoon bread crumb mixture on each mussel.
Place under broiler for a few minutes.
Serve hot!

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt. Remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.

title: lemon pepper chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Mix with other ingredients. Serve on crackers or make a sandwich with sliced tomatoes and lettuce.
You can also use canned chicken or add a cup of cooked macaroni.

title: texas watermelon sherbet
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice, salt and watermelon.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Spoon mixture into blender container and blend until smooth.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Place over low heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add to watermelon mixture and mix well.
Add whipping cream slowly while beating.
Mixture should be foamy.
Freeze.
Five cups of cantaloupe or honeydew can be substituted for the watermelon.

title: hot cheesy hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix the two cheeses.
Spread 1/2 of mixed cheeses on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chilies on top.
Spread other 1/2 of cheese on top of that, then pour beaten eggs over the top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve on wheat crackers.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Wait until completely cool before removing from pan.

title: ham casserole
directions: Brown ham and onions in butter.
Add
water
to
cheese and heat
until melted.
Then add pimentos
and
peas.	Stir. Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix.
Bake 35 minutes in casserole in 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water. Combine all remaining ingredients. Place drained broccoli in greased dish. Pour sauce over and top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: stuffed garlic bread
directions: Cut loaf in half lengthwise. Tear out soft center of bread chunks, leaving crust intact. Put crust shells on foil covered cookie sheets. Melt butter in large skillet. Stir in garlic and sesame seeds. Cook 1 to 2 minutes over medium heat, being careful not to burn the garlic. Stir in bread chunks; cook until golden brown and the butter has been absorbed. Remove from heat. In a large bowl, combine sour cream, Jack cheese, Parmesan cheese and lemon pepper. Stir in artichoke hearts, toasted bread with garlic butter and sesame seeds. Mix well and spoon back into bread shells. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove foil; bake an additional 10 minutes uncovered. Let rest 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add tomato paste and water.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Cook and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on sauce.

title: cheese potato dish
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool.
Peel and slice thin.

In saucepan over low heat, combine cheese, 1/4 cup margarine and melt. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions and seasonings. Fold into potatoes and put in greased casserole or baking dish. Dot with rest of margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly on top.
Can be made a day ahead, refrigerated, and baked the next day.

title: spanish style tuna salad
directions: Toss salad greens, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss.

title: peachy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix together all fruit in large bowl.
Add peach pie filling and chop peaches.
Mix thoroughly. Pie filling acts as dressing.

title: fruity lime jell-o salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Chill until syrupy. In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and pineapple. Stir into cooled gelatin. Fold in whipped cream, pecans and cherries. Pour into a 4-cup mold coated with non-stick cooking spray. Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight. Serves 6-8 people.

title: light and zesty chicken 'n rice
directions: *One 2-pound, cut up chicken may be substituted.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix the hamburger meat, French onion dip mix and 3/4 cup rice. Roll the mixture into meatballs, about an inch thick, then roll meatballs in remaining rice.
Pour tomato sauce over the meatballs in a baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stars and stripes dessert
directions: Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with 8 slices pound cake loaf.
Top with blueberries, strawberries and Cool Whip. Design "stars and stripes" with 3 cups halved strawberries and 1/3 cup blueberries.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.
Makes 15 servings.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cut onion into slices, then each slice out in quarters.
Saute chicken in a little oil.
When slightly browned, place in greased casserole dish.
Saute onions in a pan until limp and put in casserole with chicken.
Add rice, soup, water and half of the cheese.
Place uncovered in oven set at 350°.
Stir every 20 minutes for 1 hour, then stir again and place second cup of cheese on top.
Bake 20 more minutes or until top cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pie filling together.
Beat eggs, vanilla and oil together.
Mix all together; pour in greased pan (I use 9 x 13-inch pan).
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn (either air popped or in a stir crazy popper with 2 tablespoons of oil).
Heat syrup and drizzle over popcorn.

title: lentil soup
directions: Saute onion in butter and then add the big franks.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Spray an oblong pan with Pam and pour in ingredients.
Sprinkle with a little paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Makes a large casserole.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Place eggs and sugar in bowl.
Beat with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Add pumpkin and beat 1 minute on low speed.
On low speed, gradually add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Stir about 2 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Add cheese and sausage.
Make into balls and bake at 375° until done, turning while baking to be sure the sausage is done.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; pour over pie plate.
Bake for about 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease one cookie sheet.
Line one cookie sheet with wax paper.
Mix first six ingredients and pour on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn onto wax paper that is sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: brandied fresh fruit pot
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruits and sugars. Let stand 3 hours, stirring once or twice. Tie cinnamon in cheesecloth bag. Add to fruit along with brandy. Cover loosely or pour into a jar and cover loosely. Let stand at last 1 week, stirring once a day. Makes 12 cups.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: paprika beef stew
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons oil in large heavy kettle, add one-third of beef and brown for 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from pan and repeat with remaining meat.

title: seven layer magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order listed; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill if desired. Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.
Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to boil; remove from heat.
Slowly pour beaten eggs into soup, stirring constantly.
The egg forms lacy strands as it cooks.
Stir in scallions or onions.
Serve immediately.
Yields 1 quart.

title: pan-fried fish
directions: Mix eggs, milk, dressing, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Rinse fish fillets; pat dry with paper towel.
Soak in egg mixture and bread with crumbs.
Fry fillets in small amount of oil until golden brown.
When fillets are almost cooked, pour a capful of lemon juice in frying pan and cover.
Serve immediately.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Wrap water chestnut in 1/2 slice of bacon and fasten with toothpick.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: family favorite - kale soup
directions: Remove casing from sausage and saute over medium heat in the olive oil in a large stockpot.
Break up sausage into small pieces.
When the sausage is cooked halfway, add the onion, garlic and red bell pepper.
Season with salt and pepper.
cook until the vegetables are translucent, then pour in the chicken stock.
Bring to a boil and add the bay leaves and kale.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until the kale becomes tender.
Stir in potatoes and crushed red peppers.
Simmer 45 minutes; discard the bay leaves. Re-season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve nice and hot with crusty bread.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cucumbers with sour cream
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers very thin; sprinkle with salt and let stand, covered, at least 30 minutes.
Combine other ingredients and mix with well drained cucumbers.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate oysters
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt until well combined.
Ball into small bite sized balls and chill for 1 hour. Melt chocolate, adding 1/2 teaspoon oil if too stiff, until smooth.
Grind peanuts.
Dip balls 1 at a time into chocolate until covered.
Roll candy ball in peanuts until covered. Refrigerate until set.
Store in a cool, covered place.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs and melted butter.
Mix well; press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine powdered sugar, soft butter, eggs and salt.
Beat on high speed 15 minutes.
Don't overbeat.
Spread sugar mix on top of crushed pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over fruit and crust layers, then sprinkle with nuts and cherry halves.
Chill.

title: diabetic fruit punch
directions: In large pitcher, combine soft drink mix and water.
Mix well. Add orange juice.
Mix.
When ready to serve pour in punch bowl. Add white soda.
Makes 20 servings (5 quarts).

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend cold, then hot water into mixture of sugar, cornstarch and salt. Cook over low heat. Stir constantly until thick.
Slowly blend egg yolks. Return to heat and cook 2 minutes. Add lemon juice and rind.
Cook until desired thickness. Remove from heat. Add butter. Pour into cooked pie shell. Top with stiffly beaten meringue.

title: hot chicken or tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips, and toss lightly.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1 cup potato chips.
Heat at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Cut large cucumbers into 4-8 pieces lengthwise.
Let stand in ice water 8 hours or overnight.
Pack into hot sterilized jars. Fill each jar with 2 pieces of garlic and pickling onion.

title: crock pot chili
directions: Cook ground chuck and drain. Combine all ingredients in a crock pot and cook 4-5 hours or until done.

title: pineapple cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pineapple, celery and green pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat cream until stiff.
Add vinegar, slowly, salt and pepper.
Continue beating until well blended.
Mix with salad ingredients.
Chill.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs until light. Add oil and vanilla and beat until blended. Beat in remaining dry ingredients (except apples and nuts) for 30 seconds. By hand, mix in apples and nuts. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan for 45-60 minutes.

title: microwave turtles
directions: Put caramels, milk and oleo in a 1-quart glass measure cup. Heat on Medium to High in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes, until caramels melt.
Arrange pecans in groups of 3 on buttered baking sheet.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of warm caramel mixture over each group of pecans.
Refrigerate, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Put chocolate chips in 2-cup glass measure.
Heat on Medium for 5 to 6 minutes, until melted.
Spoon enough chocolate over carameled pecans to cover.
Allow to cool.
Remove from sheet.
Store in single layer in covered container in the refrigerator.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to the sugar and egg mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's plain chocolate candies; reserve remaining candies for decorating.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
