Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown. Makes about 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: homemade taco seasoning
directions: This recipe will make the equivalent of one store-bought taco seasoning package.

title: poor man stew
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add and combine remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on toasted bread.

title: cheesy beef ball
directions: Chop up all ingredients very fine and mix together. Form into ball and chill. Serve with assorted snack crackers.

title: oven baked brisket
directions: Put brisket (any size) in pan.
Pour 1/2 bottle of Woods Cook-In sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 275°
for 3 hours.
Turn brisket over.
Pour on other 1/2 bottle of Cook-In sauce.
Cover with foil.
Cook 3 more hours at 275°.
Cool.
Lift from liquid. Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours or more.
Heat in oven.
Slice and serve.

title: eggnog cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 round 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer pans. Combine all ingredients except frosting.
Blend on low 30 seconds, then beat on medium speed 3 minutes.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: salmon, fresh-grilled or baked
directions: Place salmon, skin side down, in baking dish which has been sprayed or greased and lined with aluminum foil.
Mix the vegetables, mushrooms, pimentos and parsley; put over fish.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over fish.
Wrap foil over fish and seal tight.
Bake or grill 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until flakes.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle the shredded cabbage with salt.
Toss well and let stand 1 hour.
Drain off any excess water.
Add the carrots and peppers and mix well.
Combine vinegar, sugar, water and seed in saucepan and boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage and spoon into freezer containers and freeze.
Thaw before serving. May be put back in the freezer and taken out when you need it again.
Will surprise you how crisp it gets.

title: gar salad
directions: Dice all vegetables and fruit.
Cut fish into 1/2-inch cubes and boil in shrimp boil until white.
Mix all together.
Serve with crackers.

title: white chili(hot)
directions: Soak and wash beans.
Cover with water to 2 inches above beans.
Let soak overnight.
Drain beans; place in heavy kettle. Add to beans the soup base, onion, garlic and salt.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours; stir occasionally.
Add chicken, chillies, cumin, oregano and pepper.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over each bowl of soup as it is served.

title: pecan bars
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
Cream together.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Cook at 350° until lightly brown and inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix together lemon supreme cake mix, beaten eggs and Cool Whip. Drop small amounts of dough from teaspoon into powdered sugar without much handling of dough, make sure each drop of dough is coated with powdered sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: sausage macaroni bake
directions: In a large skillet in oil, saute chopped garlic clove.
Remove and discard garlic.
Add chopped onion to pan and saute until translucent.
Remove sauteed onion to large casserole.
Saute sausage pieces; remove and drain well.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, apples, carrots, pineapple, onion and raisins.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to liquid ingredients, mixing gradually on medium speed.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This recipe makes 2 cakes for a large crowd.

title: chipped beef dip(from estill's baby girl)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 15-20 minutes.
Best served on Ritz crackers.

title: chip and cheese fish fillets
directions: In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange fillets with thicker portions toward edge of dish.
Turn under thin portions to obtain even thickness.
Spoon salad dressing over fish.
Pat on crushed chips.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; boil 5 minutes, stirring all the time.
Add vanilla when removed from heat.
Serve hot or cold.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs before adding.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 400° until top is brown, then bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour.

title: pickle roll-em-ups
directions: Spread 1 side of each ham slice with 1 tablespoon cream cheese.
Place 1 pickle on edge of each ham slice.
Roll ham slice around pickle; press edges to seal.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Cut each piece into 6 slices.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers, cheeses, etc.

title: simple lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Mix the lemon pie filling in with the dry angel food cake mix.
Bake in a 9x13 baking pan for 30 minutes. If desired, bars can be topped with chopped nuts or coconut.

title: chicken salad tea sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, mayonnaise and olives.
Spread each slice of bread with 1 teaspoon butter, then with 3 tablespoons chicken salad mixture.
Trim crusts and cut each slice crosswise into four finger sandwiches.
Yield:
16 open-faced finger sandwiches.

title: alberta red-eye stew
directions: Dredge beef with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil.
Add onions and garlic; cook until onions are transparent.
Add beer, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, steak sauce, thyme and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat; simmer for 1 hour.
Add tomato juice; simmer for 30 minutes. Add peas; simmer for 10 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Put Marshmallow Creme in large mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, water and salt in pan and bring to rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes. Pour into Marshmallow Creme and beat until candy loses its luster. Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat to mix, and drop onto wax paper from teaspoon.
Let set to cool.

title: cheese buttons
directions: Mix cheese, 1 egg, salt and pepper and set aside.
Knead together flour, milk and 1 egg.
Roll dough thin and cut into 3 or 4 inch squares.
Put 1 tablespoon cheese mixture on square, fold over and seal edges.
Slowly cook in salted water or chicken broth 10 to 15 minutes or until they rise to the top.
Take out and let drain.
Fry in butter until brown.

title: kringla
directions: Cream together sugar, egg and butter.
Add buttermilk and mix. Add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate dough overnight.
Using a spoonful of dough, roll into a pencil thin strip.
Form into figure 8 and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove only 1/4 of dough from fridge at a time.

title: fish soup
directions: Chop green onions and celery.
Saute onions and celery.
In a large soup pan, add fillets to vegetables.
Add all ingredients, juices from clams, crabmeat and shrimp.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for half-hour to heat through.

title: easy taco salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put chopped onion on top.
Then add shredded lettuce.
Add tomatoes and shredded cheese just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: missy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Spoon into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili con quesa
directions: Mix and put in crock-pot or bake 45 minutes at 275° or until melted.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, celery, onion, water chestnuts, green pepper, pimiento, mayonnaise and lemon juice in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover.
Microwave 10 minutes on #8 setting, stirring after 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with corn chips and cheese.
Microwave 1 minute on High or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese bread
directions: Soften the yeast in milk.
Mix together the flour, sugar and salt.
Combine the potatoes, melted butter, cheese and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat until well blended and add the yeast mixture and dry ingredients.
Knead on floured board 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down and knead again for 2 minutes. Shape into a long roll and place in a well-greased angel food cake pan, pinching ends of dough together.
Cover and let rise again for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes.
Turn out onto foil; brush with butter for soft crust.

title: red cabbage with apples
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Stir in cabbage, apple, salt, caraway seed, pepper, brown sugar, vinegar and water.
Cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes, or until cabbage is tender and flavors are well blended.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grilled pork loin
directions: Separate halves.
Rub equal amounts of herb on both pieces of meat.
Tie halves together.
Grill over medium coals for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Best results obtained by using rotisserie.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Cook a few minutes.
Add tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Line a large baking dish with a layer of noodles, a layer of meat sauce, then a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: In a good size baking dish, layer 1/2 rice, corn and tomato sauce with 1/2 cup water, onion, green pepper, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Put remainder of rice, corn,
tomato sauce and 3/4 cup water on first layer.
Place bacon across top and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing (see recipe).

title: salad dressing
directions: Shake well in a covered jar.
Is especially good on spinach salad.

title: homemade bread stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter in skillet until tender.
Add mixture to bread in large bowl.
Sprinkle with seasonings, which have been combined.
Add broth and egg.
Mix well.
Stuff bird immediately and roast.
Makes 9 cups, enough to stuff a 12 pound bird.
(Add more broth if not moist enough.)

title: ladyfinger cream cake
directions: Line bottom and sides of spring-form pan (9-inch) with ladyfingers.
Whip cream.
Whip cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Whip cheese and cream together carefully.
Pour mixture into pan. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with any flavor pie filling and chill thoroughly.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Mix together and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks and mash.
Add vinegar and other ingredients.
Refill egg whites.
Garnish with paprika. Yields 16 deviled eggs.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together cream cheese, vanilla and margarine. Slowly add powdered sugar until smooth.

title: pickled black-eyed peas
directions: Drain liquid from peas.
Place	peas
in
pan
or bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Remove garlic bud
after
one
day.
Store	at least two days and put to two weeks before eating.	Red kidney beans and garbanzo beans may be substituted.
Do the same way.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Bring potatoes to a boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until soft and drain.
In large bowl, beat potatoes with mixer until smooth.
Add beaten eggs, 1/4 cup of the brown sugar, 1/4 cup of the oleo, salt and cinnamon.
Add orange juice slowly and beat until fluffy.
Scrape potatoes into large dish and smooth surface. Arrange pecans on top.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of sugar over pecans.
Drizzle top with remaining 1/4 cup of oleo (melted). Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Mixture should be very moist. Form into small balls and roll each meat ball in flour to cover. Brown
in
melted
margarine.
Pour
water and beef broth over meat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Split
zucchini
lengthwise;
scoop
out
all of center pulp and
seeds.
Chop and put aside.
Saute beef and onion in oil; drain fat.	Add rest of ingredients except margarine and cheese. Mix in pulp; pile into scooped out centers.
Top with margarine and
cheese.
Bake	at
until tender (about 1 hour).

title: wonder fudge
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and butter together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix well.
Put into 2 greased 9 x 13-inch pans.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in microwave to heat thoroughly.
Serve with dip size Fritos.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the 3/4 cup boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add the mashed banana, strawberries and pineapple with juice to the jello.
Pour half of mixture into a serving bowl; put into refrigerator to set.
When set, spread sour cream over and then pour remaining jello mixture over top of sour cream.
Let set completely.
Serve.

title: spring asparagus salad
directions: Trim off white ends of asparagus; slice diagonally.
Bring water to a boil and boil asparagus 3 to 5 minutes until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and marinate asparagus at least 1 hour.
Serve cold.

title: delicious hot cocoa
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, water and salt. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until cocoa dissolves. Stir in milk.
Cover over medium heat until hot.
Do not boil! Makes four 9-ounce servings.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand for 24 hours.
Boil the remaining ingredients just to boiling point and then add the vegetables to marinate.
Keep in refrigerator for 12 hours before use.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs. Beat together. Add vanilla, salt and soda. Beat together with flour. Stir in oatmeal. Drop by spoon (heaping teaspoon) onto nonstick cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini appetizer or bread
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together. Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until brown.
Serve warm.

title: quiche
directions: Mix
everything
together
and	pour
into a (deep pie) shell. Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: For frosting, melt first 4 ingredients and boil for 1 minute. Add vanilla and let cool.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Mix boiling water and jello; let stand; add nuts.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine, mix with cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bulgur natural casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Bake, covered.
The last 5 minutes, add triangles of Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: v-4 tomato juice
directions: Cut up tomatoes and place in 12-quart kettle, heat until hot. Gradually add chopped vegetables, always maintaining a boil.
Add sugar, salt and spices.
Simmer 20 minutes; uncovered.
Put through food mill.
Pour hot juice in hot jars leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Pressure can at 5 pounds for 15 minutes for pints or 20 minutes for quarts.

title: chili skillet(yields 4 servings)
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook beef, onion, peppers and garlic until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain fat.
Add tomato juice, kidney beans, chili powder, salt and rice; cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in corn and olives; cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and cook only until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Beat well, then add flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Cool and cover with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and bell pepper.
Drain well.
Add beans and rice.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve with cheese and chips.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix ingredients and add garlic salt or powder and dash of Worcestershire sauce.

title: hawaiian shrimp
directions: Saute celery, onion and pepper until soft.
Add pineapple chunks, juice, vinegar, soya sauce and cornstarch.
Add shrimp; let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.
Double for family.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Roll in 1/2 package of chipped ham or nuts.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, spices, salt, baking powder, soda and sugar.
Add shortening, bananas and eggs.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Fold in rolled oats.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: patio baked beans
directions: Set beans aside for now.
Mix all ingredients, except for onion and bacon, together.
Heat for 5 minutes until smooth. Slice onion into thin slices and cut bacon into 1-inch pieces. Use 2-quart casserole.
Arrange alternate layers of baked beans, onion and beans.
Pour hot sugar mixture over.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; add bacon to top and bake, uncovered, for 30 more minutes.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix together with mixer; form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts; chill.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix and set aside food coloring and Nestle Quik.
Mix well so you don't have bits of chocolate pieces.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and the color paste.
Beat 10 minutes (YES - 10 MINUTES).
Add buttermilk and slowly add flour, then salt and vanilla.
Remove from mixer.
Mix vinegar and soda in a cup separately and mix well.
Add to mixture by hand.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans that are greased and floured for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple, cherries and boil. Make it 1 cup by adding water, if needed. Add jello, cream cheese, pineapple, cherries and nuts. Mix well. Add 2 small Coca-Colas and congeal.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions
for 5 minutes after water returns to a boil; drain.
Gently fold mushroom soup into drained onions.
Melt margarine; mix in bread crumbs and sprinkle over onion mixture. Spray casserole dish with nonstick shortening; bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cut together first 3 ingredients as for pie crust.
Sprinkle evenly over 12 or 13-inch pizza pan.
Press firmly and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise, onion, egg, salt and pepper with squash.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs, grated cheese and melted butter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into large bowl.
Combine margarine, baking cocoa, shortening and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add to flour mixture; mix well. Add eggs, vanilla, soda and buttermilk; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 18-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour frosting over hot cake.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: ermine icing
directions: Cook
flour
and milk until thick, stirring constantly. Cool until completely cold.
Add sugar, shortening and vanilla and beat until
icing is of spreading consistency.	It should be fluffy, almost like whipped cream.

title: one hour turkey
directions: You will need one turkey browning bag.

title: apricot chicken
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine preserves, soy sauce, lemon juice, onion, parsley and oregano.
Add chicken pieces and turn several times, coating them well with sauce.
Refrigerate overnight, turning pieces several times.
Remove from sauce and place in a single layer in a baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender and lightly browned. Brush with sauce several times during cooking.
Brush remaining sauce on chicken just before serving.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise on (lightly greased) 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides of pan; seal perforations.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Spread sour cream over crust.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with remaining ingredients; drizzle buttermilk dressing over top of pizza; cut into squares.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: pineapple ham balls
directions: Combine ham, pork and bread crumbs.
Add eggs and pepper. Mix well.
Chill.
Form into 10 balls and set aside.
Drain pineapple and reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Put juice and sugar in saucepan.
Add vinegar and mustard.
Cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Arrange pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Place a ham ball on each slice.
Pour sugar mixture over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Beat oil, club soda and eggs together.
Add cake mix and nuts. Mix 5 minutes with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in a tube pan, greased and floured.
Cool.

title: pineapple cheer
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Bring to a boil and add pineapple and sugar.
Combine this with the jello.
Cool.
Then add miniature marshmallows.
Let stand until it begins to jell. Then add pecans, Cool Whip and grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix and chill.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine candy and 1/4 cup melted margarine in a saucepan. Place over low heat until melted.
Stir constantly; cool.
Cream sugar and 1/2 cup softened margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Add to cream mixture.
Add flour, beating well.
Stir in candy bars and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf(no eggs)
directions: Mix well the ground beef, dry milk, onion, bread (torn into small bits), Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Put into small loaf pan and pour remaining tomato sauce over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, salt, dry mustard and milk together.
Layer in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish the bread, sausage, cheese and then egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread in a bag
directions: You will need 1 heavy duty 1 gallon Ziploc freezer bag.

title: cottage cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs and stir in cottage cheese.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour into a buttered baking dish and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook all ingredients in large pot for 4 hours.
Remove meat from juice and slice.
Place back in juice.
If chuck roast is used, remove fat and separate meat in small pieces.

title: tabooley
directions: Cover wheat with cold water; let stand 30 minutes.
Drain; press out as much water as possible.
Place wheat, parsley, tomatoes, mint and green onions in a glass or plastic bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over wheat mixture.
Toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Garnish with ripe olives if desired. Recipe will feed 6.

title: hot pepper sauce
directions: Put spices in cheesecloth bag and add to other ingredients which have been pre-mixed.
Cook until peppers are soft (preferably outdoors).
Remove spice bag.
Mash mixture through a strainer or fine colander to remove skin and seeds.
Keeps indefinitely in typical hot sauce bottle with shaker top.

title: fruit ham steak
directions: Combine butter, orange juice, brown sugar and curry powder. Peel bananas and cut into 1-inch chunks.
Peel and slice peaches. Add bananas, peaches and pineapple to curry mixture.
Stir to coat. Place ham in baking dish.
Spoon fruit mix over ham.
Sprinkle coconut and cherries over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until ham and fruit are cooked and coconut is lightly browned.

title: fast, drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and cream until fluffy. Blend in milk.
Add dry ingredients. `Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with the bottom of a glass which has been dipped in sugar. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: coconut carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Add pineapple, carrots, coconut, and nuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Frost with Coconut Cream Frosting.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain and squeeze to remove all water.
Combine all other ingredients, except tomato and Parmesan cheese.
Stir lightly with fork.
Stir in spinach.
Pour into pastry shell.
Arrange tomato on top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Slice squash after washing.
Also wash potatoes and slice and put in frying pan.
Add squash and onion (sliced).
Salt and pepper.
Put in about 2 cups of water.
Cover and simmer until tender; drain water and lay cheese slices on top.
Ready to serve.

title: marinade for steak
directions: Mix dry ingredients and rub onto both sides of steak.
Mix liquids and pour over meat.
Marinate for 12-24 hours.

title: magic biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water and set aside.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Place the egg whites, sugar, cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut in a large bowl. Stir to combine. Pour the mixture into the unbaked pie shell and place in oven. Bake until glossy and set, 25 to 30 minutes. The pie will be firm around the edges but moist and chewy in the center. Let the pie cool, then slice and serve with fresh fruit and Cool Whip. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: spicy bacon-bean pot
directions: In Dutch oven, combine beans, corn, bacon, onion, pepper, barbecue sauce, chili powder and garlic powder.
Cover and cook over medium heat 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 20 servings.

title: trout with almonds
directions: Roll the trout in the seasoned flour.
Melt 4 tablespoons of the butter in a large frying pan.
Fry the trout for about 5 minutes on each side or until well browned and cooked.
Transfer the fish to a large serving dish and keep hot.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa. Add eggs and mix well. Stir in milk and vanilla.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in large pan; add cereal.
Spread on cookie sheet and cool in fridge.
Break mixture into small pieces after dried.
Soften ice cream; fold in all but 1 cup of cereal mixture.
Spread in a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Use remaining 1 cup cereal mixture to decorate top.
Garnish with whipped cream and strawberries, if desired.

title: moussaka a la grecque(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Peel the eggplants and cut them into slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Brown the slices quickly in 4 tablespoons of the butter. Set aside.
Heat 4 tablespoons of butter in the same skillet and cook the onions until they are brown.
Add the ground meat and cook 10 minutes.
Combine the tomato paste with the wine, parsley, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Stir this mixture into the meat and simmer over low heat, stirring frequently, until all the liquid has been absorbed.
Remove the mixture from heat.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: sour cream spice layer cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost.
Top with chocolate glaze and walnut halves.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute pork, onions, celery and 1/2 stick butter.
Stir in flour. Add potatoes and enough water to barely cover potatoes.
Cook, but leave slightly firm.
Add clam juice and minced clams.
Add remaining butter.
Add cayenne, white, and black peppers.
(Always taste before adding salt.)
Add cream.
Heat, but do not boil. Stir in cheese.
Place in bowls.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with chopped green onion.
Serve with crackers, use oyster crackers if available.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: You also need 24 cupcake liners.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: sweet and sour cukes(cucumber)
directions: Slice one large cuke very thin using slaw cutter.
Place in bowl.
Add onion, sliced thin (if desired).
Mix balance of ingredients and pour over cuke and onion.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine yeast, sugar and warm water; stir until completely dissolved.
Add melted butter and salt; stir.
Gradually add flour until it makes a pliable dough.
Turn out on a dough board that has 2 cups flour on it.
Knead until dough is stiff.
Place in a greased bowl; brush with oleo.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again.
Then make into rolls.
Place in pan and let rise.
Bake at 400°.
Makes 30 rolls or 2 loaves.

title: tang tea
directions: Mix tea with Tang in 2-quart container.
Add enough water to fill container.
Great thirst quencher, even without ice.

title: baked green beans
directions: Bake in casserole at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Scrunch more onions over top and serve.

title: debbie's sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
After the 3 hours, roll out and shape.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Yield is 3 dozen.

title: apple daffle cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to first mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Remove via oven.
Pour on topping.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a casserole pan, place refried beans and then tamales (be sure to remove paper wrappers).
Cover tamales with chopped onion and salsa.
Finally, cover with cheese.
Cook in oven at 450° about 15 minutes until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly. Serve with nacho chips and lettuce salad.

title: glorious frozen salad
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Blend the remaining ingredients carefully.
Put into mold or any suitable freezing bowl.
Freeze.

title: mari's green and gold sauerkraut salad
directions: Thoroughly rinse the sauerkraut with warm water.
Drain.
Mix with onions, celery, carrot and green pepper.
In a saucepan, mix the vinegar, oil, sugar and water.
Heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour while still warm over sauerkraut mixture and mix well.
Cover and chill 6 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Top with Cheddar cheese.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Beat all together.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 375° oven. Keeps 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies with mint
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
You may need a little more flour if it sticks to your hands (add 1 tablespoon at a time).
Form into balls the size of an olive and put on a cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar (they spread).
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown and firm to the touch.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: kids play dough (not edible)
directions: Mix together all ingredients; cook for 3 to 5 minutes over low heat until it forms a soft ball stage. Be sure to cook long enough. Add food coloring to water before cooking, not after. May wish to add a few drops of flavoring to make it smell good. Store in airtight container or Ziploc bag.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Place in large buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place over potatoes and spread soup over chops.
Pour 1 can of water over soup, cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: crab stroganoff
directions: Prepare egg noodles as label directs.
Meanwhile, in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot butter or margarine, cook mushrooms, stirring frequently, until all liquid is absorbed.
Stir undiluted cream of mushroom soup, milk and wine into cooked mushrooms (if not using wine, increase milk to 1 1/4 cups).
Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce boils.
Reduce heat to medium; add crabmeat, frozen peas and sour cream; heat through (do not boil!).
Add salt.
Mix parsley with noodles; arrange on large platter.
Top with crabmeat mixture; toss before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender; remove skin and bones.
Cut into bite sized pieces.
They should yield about 4 1/2 cups meat.

title: old-fashioned hot cocoa
directions: Microwaved:
Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add 3 tablespoons milk; mix well.
Heat in microwave for 30 seconds.
Remove and stir well.
Add remaining milk and heat in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and stir again.
Add marshmallows, if desired.

title: parmesan fettucini
directions: Boil fettucini noodles.
Mix sour cream and Parmesan cheese. Pour mixture over noodles and serve. You may want to add chicken chunks or crab meat to sauce mix.

title: bev's tater soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until tender.
Add bouillon cubes or broth and cook until dissolved.
Add cream of chicken soup and melted cheese and cook until heated.
Serve with cornbread.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: 1. Place Potatoes in a large bowl, add cold water to cover, let stand for 15 minutes.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Saute onion and celery until tender (not brown).
Place 1/2 of the noodles in bottom of baking dish.
Layer sprouts, celery, onion, chicken and soup, then rest of noodles.
Top with cashews. Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: vi's fabulous internationally famous salsa(canada and england count, don't they?!)
directions: In a large bowl, dice tomatoes and onion into chunky size pieces.

Chop cilantro into fine pieces (you'll know you have chopped the cilantro fine enough when your fingers are going numb from chopping so much, and there is a shooting pain in your back from leaning over the chopping board!!).
Add to bowl, along with can of tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Here comes the fun part...add the garlic until your spouse, who is sitting in the next room yells, "are we expecting vampires, or are you redecorating with strings of garlic?
The words don't have to be exact, as long as the meaning is there.
Generously sprinkle the Nile Spice.
I sprinkle until my left arm is as tired from sprinkling, as my right arm is from chopping (if you're left handed, visa versa that statement!).
Salt and pepper that puppy, easy on the salt now, the purpose of salsa is to blow the top off of the roof of your mouth, not elevate your blood pressure!
Dump in hot sauce until your eyes are burning, perhaps a little less if you're not fond of hot things.
Mix thoroughly again.
Chill.
This is most important!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Mix with other ingredients and simmer.

title: spicy coconut pears
directions: Drain pears and reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine 1/4 cup liquid, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Put mixture over pears.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Into large pan, cover with water (small amount) onions, celery and parsley flakes.
Cook until almost done.
Add tomatoes.
Cook until done.
Add butter, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add flour mixed in enough water to make paste.
Cook 5 minutes.
Run mixture through a sieve.
Fill jars and process in water bath for 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour this mixture over butter.
Pour drained peaches (or other fruit) in middle.
Do not stir!
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wacky snow cones
directions: Put sugar, sweetened mix and water in a bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour the mixture over crushed ice in cups or bowls.

title: marzitta
directions: Cook beef
and
onion
in
small amount of oil; chop in celery.
Cook
noodles
in
big pan until tender;
drain.
Mix last 4
ingredients into 1 cup of juice; mix well.
Pour meat, celery and
noodles, peas and all of juice together; mix well. Put in dish
and
cook
30 minutes at 350°.
Put cheese on top and cook 30 minutes more.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in egg whites.
Put in greased pan and bake in oven at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Pie will be light brown when done. Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or cool whip.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Place
cranberries
in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with apples
and pineapple.
Mix sugar, oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and
pecans.
Spread over fruit.
Pour melted margarine over
the top.
Bake	at
350° until brown, about 30 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pressure cooker spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Brown spareribs in frying pan with oil or under broiler. Place trivet in pressure cooker. Pour in water and add sauerkraut, onions and spareribs. Cook at high pressure for 1 hour.
Serve with your choice of potato, etc.

title: easy does it doughnuts
directions: Place biscuits on wax paper and cut out centers.
When shortening is hot, put biscuits in pan and brown on both sides. Brown the cutout centers also.
Drain on paper towels.
Mom's can let the kids do the rest.
Put the powdered sugar in a brown lunch sack and the cinnamon sugar mixture in another.
Put a cooked doughnut in the sack and let the kids shake it up until coated all over.

title: joy's appetizer meatballs
directions: 1. In bowl combine the first twelve ingredients.

Mix well. 2. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on rack in a shallow roasting pan. 3. Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes. 4. Remove meatballs and drain rack. 5. Combine ketchup and cornstarch in roasting pan. 6. Stir in jellies and add meatballs and bake for 30-35 miutes at 300°.

title: lemon cool whip pie
directions: Stir all together. Beat with mixer on high until creamy.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter cups(good, but easy)
directions: *Use both or just use all margarine; best with half butter.

title: beef and tater bake
directions: Put meat in 8-inch square pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain fat.
Combine hot potatoes and 3/4 cup cheese and spread over meat.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and chill.

title: willard's hamburgers
directions: Put hamburger patty in water.
Let boil until done.
Put mustard and onions on bun.
Dip top bun in juice from skillet.

title: hawaiian mochi
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix mochi flour with baking powder. Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour coconut milk and evaporated milk into a large glass measure.
Add enough water to make 1 quart liquid total.
With mixer running, gradually add milk mixture to creamed mixture alternately with flour and baking powder mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 1 hour or until a wood pick inserted in center comes out nearly clean.
Cool, then cut into 24 pieces.

title: meringue peaches(light dessert)
directions: Combine egg whites (at room temperature) in a large bowl at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Sprinkle salt, cream of tartar and vanilla over egg whites; continue beating until soft peak forms.
Gradually add sugar, a tablespoon at a time, and cornstarch, beating until stiff peaks form.
Place peach halves, cut side down in six 10-ounce custard cups.
Spread peaches evenly with meringue.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Yields six servings, 103 calories and 1.4 g fat per serving.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheets with aluminum foil. In a large bowl, beat eggs well.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and flour; blend well. (This is a thin mixture.) Drop from a teaspoon onto the cookie sheets.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes, until lightly browned around the edges.
Remove from cookie sheets and cool.

title: crispy baked fillets(reduced fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash and dry fillets and cut into pieces.
Season, dip in oil and coat in crumbs.
Arrange in shallow, lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes without turning or basting.
Serves 4. Contains 260 calories.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4 inch thickness. In a non-stick skillet, cook chicken in oil over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until juices run clear. Sprinkle with lemon juice, rosemary, oregano and pepper.

title: apple salad
directions: Prepare jello.
Slightly congeal.
Add rest of the ingredients and fold in well.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold.

title: confetti ice cream punch
directions: To make punch base:
Mix fruit punch with water and chill. If an ice ring is desired, freeze a portion of this base mixture in a ring jello mold until slushy, 1 to 2 hours.
Remove from freezer and place strawberries in the ring at even intervals. Return to freezer until serving time.
When ready to serve, pour base mixture into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and softened ice cream.
Stir until the ice cream dissolves.
Unmold ice ring and place gently into center of the punch bowl.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove and cook spaghetti in broth until most of broth is gone.
Add soup, mushrooms, cheese, butter, seasonings and boned chicken to spaghetti.
Cook very low until it obtains desired consistency.

title: mom's five bean salad
directions: In a jar, shake together the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Put beans, pepper, celery, pimento and onion rings in a bowl and pour liquid mixture over this.
Mix well and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: shawarma
directions: Slice beef into long, thin strips.
Mix ingredients together and marinade meat overnight.
Cover meat and bake for 1 hour at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or with pita bread.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 half-baked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done in middle.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup coconut and 1 cup pecans in bottom.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over coconut and pecans.

title: kielbasi bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: flounder au gratin
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan over low heat.
Add onions and celery; saute until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; stir well.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add shredded Swiss cheese; reduce heat and cook until cheese melts, continuing to stir.
Set aside.
Arrange fillets in single layer in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray. Pour cheese mixture evenly over fillets.
Cover; bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until fish flake easily.
Sprinkle with parsley. Yields 4 servings.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
If dough is sticky, add flour to handle.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on well floured pastry cloth; cut out with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased bakery sheets.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: st. patrick's day pie
directions: Place pineapple and pudding mix ina mixing bowl and mix well. Put in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell and put in the refrigerator for 30 minutes before serving.

title: seafood fancy
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Turn into 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: quick pimento salad
directions: Let pineapple drain.
Combine with other ingredients and serve.

title: potluck favorite
directions: Brown hamburger, celery, onions and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Add dry ingredients and beat 1 to 2 minutes and then beat in fat.
Separate (1/4-inch thick) onion slices
into
rings
and dip in batter.
Drop rings into hot fat until golden brown.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine salt, squash, onion and peppers.
Mix sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add all ingredients to syrup in pan and let boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Allow 6 to 8 weeks to make.

title: oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Heat sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in pot until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat. Cool for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients. Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Combine ingredients in a bag.
Wash and drain chicken.
Coat with flour mixture and fry in an iron skillet.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in order listed. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Brown meat; drain. Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder. Layer half each of the meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole. Repeat layers. Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: elbow casserole
directions: Cook elbows and drain.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Add milk slowly until sauce thickens.
Add shredded cheese.
Fry hamburger and drain.
Combine with elbows.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sauce and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar and baking powder. Stir in cornmeal. Add eggs, milk and oil. Beat just until mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil; stir constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: butter babies
directions: Combine Bisquick and cream, stirring until well mixed.
Turn dough onto surface lightly sprinkled with Bisquick and pat out to 1/2-inch thickness.
(Dough will be sticky.) Cut with 1-inch round cutter.
Melt butter in a pan with sides in 350° oven.
Dip each biscuit (both sides) into butter and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Bring macaroni to a boil in 1 1/2 quarts of water and 1 t salt.
Stir frequently, then turn to low heat and cook for 20 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until delicately browned; remove.
Drain excess fat, reserving 1/4 cup in skillet.
Add flour, sugar, salt and pepper; blend well.
Beat egg slightly.
Add vinegar, water and lemon juice.
Add gradually to mixture in skillet; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients; toss lightly.

title: spaghetti squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; scoop out seeds.
Place with cut side down in a baking dish; add water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until it is easily pierced with a fork. When cool enough to handle, scoop out squash, separating the strands with a fork.

title: chicken barbecue sauce(indiana state grand champion)
directions: Combine ingredients together in saucepan.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Wash
chops.
Salt and pepper.	Place in shallow baking dish. Place one slice of onion on top of pork chops; salt and pepper. Place
slice of tomato on top of onion.
Season.
Put enough water in pan to cover bottom.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add water, if needed.

title: chocolate pudding delight
directions: Blend flour, oleo, sugar and nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 22 minutes at 350° and let cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix powdered sugar and 1/2 of the Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Mix puddings 1 at a time with 1 1/2 cups milk each and spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with grated Hershey bar or finely chopped nuts.

title: cinnamon apples (microwave)
directions: Place apples in microwave safe dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and place butter on top.
Microwave for 5 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wipe chicken well with paper towels.
Combine lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, garlic, paprika, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add chicken.
Coat each piece well. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: smoked turkey baked chimichangas
directions: Preheat your toaster oven to 400°.
Place turkey in a bowl and season with chili powder.
Add shredded cabbage, chipotles in adobo, tomato sauce, scallions.
Toss filling to combine and season with salt and pepper.
Place tortillas in a kitchen towel and set in microwave.
Microwave on high for 1 minute.
To build, place a generous handful of cheese near one edge of the tortilla.
Pile 1/4 of your filling in the tortilla. tuck sides up and roll tortilla tightly.
Repeat to make 4 large tortilla wraps.
Brush the toaster oven baking tray with vegetable or olive oil.
Brush the wraps with oil and bake until deep golden all over, 15 to 17 minutes.
Top with sour cream, cilantro or parsley and chopped orange or yellow tomatoes, as garnishes.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Combine potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in potato water and add to potato mixture.
Stir in baking powder and flour and let stand until mixture begins to rise.
Work in additional flour so that dough can be handled and kneaded.
Pinch off amount needed and shape rolls.
Put remainder in the refrigerator.
Form into rolls of desired shape and size.
Sweet rolls and rings may be made by adding fruits, nuts and spices as desired.
Bake at 450° until browned.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or 2 knives. Combine remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture.
Mix until it forms a ball.
Makes enough for 4 or 5 crusts, depending on size of pan.

title: one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, meat and onion powder in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: quick chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion and butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in chicken, 1/2 cup of picante sauce and cumin.
Heat through. Remove from heat; stir in 1 cup of the cheese.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides and arrange in a 2-quart casserole. Slice onions to 1/4-inch slices.
Place on top of chops.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Heat water and bouillon cube to a boil. Add broccoli and carrot. Cook according to package directions and remove from heat. Do not drain.

title: quick hamburger meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into muffin pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan on medium heat and cook until mixture comes away from the pan.
Cool.
Then knead out lumps.
Store in sealed container. Cooked play dough has a longer shelf life and a better consistency than uncooked play dough.

title: banana split breakfast
directions: On small plate arrange the banana as a banana split and brush each with 1/4 teaspoon of lemon juice.
Spoon the cottage cheese onto the banana, pour the melted jam over the cheese and sprinkle the sunflower seeds on top.

title: sweet potatoes in apple shells
directions: Halve apples crosswise; remove core and seeds.
Sprinkle cavity with brown sugar.
Place in shallow pan containing small amount of water.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a shell about 1/2-inch thick.
Add mashed apple pulp, butter and cream to hot, mashed sweet potatoes.
Beat until fluffy.
Put mixture in apple shells; sprinkle with pecans.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend eggs, cornbread mix and oil together. Add remaining ingredients and pour in greased baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread on cookie sheet the dinner rolls, pinching edges together.
Bake until golden brown and cool.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cool carrots and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and add carrots.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Keeps a long time in refrigerator.

title: easy dinner
directions: Using a large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, salt, pepper, water, potatoes and margarine. Bring to a boil.
Add the noodles while stirring until the mixture resumes boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until potatoes and noodles are done, stirring occasionally.
Add your choice of carrots and peas 1 to 2 minutes before mixture is done.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Place cabbage, salt, sugar, vinegar and caraway seed in a large saucepan.
Cover with water; simmer for 30 minutes, until cabbage is softened.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 side dish servings. Preparation time:
10 to 15 minutes.
Cooking time:
30 minutes.

title: six-layer dip
directions: Mash avocados in a bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Then combine sour cream and mayonnaise in another bowl.

title: classic chocolate cream pie
directions: Bake pastry shell; set aside.

title: ice cream cookie freakout
directions: In food processor or blender, crush cookies slightly.
Add ice cream in scoops and process until smooth.

title: donna's fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk.
Cook until forms soft ball.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan.

title: 10 minute chicken-mushroom dinner
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Place all ingredients, except rice, in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir and cook 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Easy and delicious!

title: lemon cool whip pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together well. Add the Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: shrimp bayou
directions: Drain tomatoes, measuring liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 1 1/3 cups.
Brown celery, green pepper and onion in butter.
Add shrimp; cook until pink.
Add liquid, tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper, bay leaf, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes more. Remove bay leaf and parsley.
Serve hot.
Very good.

title: cheerio drops
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients together in double boiler.
Add 1 cup dry roasted peanuts and 2 cups Cheerios.
Mix; drop on wax paper.

title: good and easy cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add dressing and mix until well mixed. Roll into 2 balls or 1 big ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate.
Keeps well for several ways.
Serve with any kind of crackers.

title: school rice krispie squares
directions: Warm first 4 ingredients until hot and bubbly.
Mix in cereal. Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press to cover.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: spicy potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes. Cube into bite size pieces. Boil until almost done. Drain water and put into a casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients (except onion rings). Pour over potatoes. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle onion rings on top the last 5 minutes of baking. Makes 8 servings.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Place paper liners in 18 muffin cups; put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla; beat until smooth and creamy.
Fill each muffin cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Put a teaspoon of pie filling on top of each cheesecake.
If desired, top with whipped cream.

title: baked mustard chicken
directions: Brush chicken with mustard and dredge in bread crumbs.
Place in a baking dish.
Combine butter, lemon juice and water; drizzle 1 tablespoon over each piece of chicken and pour remainder in dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove cover, sprinkle with paprika and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 2 or 4.

title: switchel
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Let it cool.

title: sand cups
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping. Gradually stir in 1 cup of crushed wafers.
Top with remaining crushed wafers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Decorate just before serving.
Put in 8 to 10 plastic cups.

title: holiday vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables. Mix vinegar, sugar and oil and bring to a boil. Cool. Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 1 stick butter in 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Make a batter with first four ingredients.
Mix well and pour batter back and forth over melted butter.
Do not stir. Use fruit of your choice.
Use fruit syrup also.
Do not stir. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain fruit and save juice.
Mix juice with sugar, salt and flour.
Cook together until thickened.
Beat eggs and add.
Set overnight.
In the morning add oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: potato soup
directions: In large sauce pan, combine potatoes, onion, Crisco, salt & pepper.
Add water to cover about 1-inch over.
Cook on med until tender.
Mix corn starch with 1/2 c. water, add to boiling potatoes to thicken.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in an 8 x 10-inch casserole dish. Set aside. Cream the margarine and gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat well. Add flour to creamed mixture and mix well. Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour batter over peaches.
Combine the remaining 3/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in boiling water, stirring until sugar melts.
Pour over batter. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the reserved oleo and bread crumbs.
Put in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle top with bread crumbs, then add the oleo and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This would serve 10 to 12 people.

title: tomato bisque
directions: Combine tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, onion, bacon crumbles, sugar, bay leaves, garlic, chicken bouillon, V - 8 juice, salt and pepper in a large sauce pan. Mix well.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve hot with homemade croutons.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Cut two 15 x 12-inch pieces of heavy-duty foil.
Place a chicken breast in center of each. Top with onion and remaining ingredients. Wrap well.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 servings (221 calories per serving).

title: spicy baked shrimp(serves 6)
directions: Combine garlic, butter, salt, marjoram and Tabasco; cream together.
Add bread crumbs and sherry and toss until well blended.
Add shrimp and toss until shrimp are lightly coated with crumb mixture.
Divide shrimp among separate baking dishes and sprinkle with chopped parsley, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Lightly squeeze lemon wedges over shrimp, if desired, and serve with additional lemon wedges.
Garnish with sprigs of fresh parsley.
This recipe is also great using sea scallops instead of shrimp!

title: nutritious kool-aid punch
directions: Mix ingredients together in a gallon container.
Shake well. Add water to fill the container.

title: quick and easy sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Prepare meatballs and fry until cooked all the way through. Drain grease from meatballs.
Combine sauce and jelly in crock-pot.
After jelly has completely dissolved, add meatballs to sauce and cook on low for about 1 hour.

title: layered green salad
directions: In a deep clear bowl, layer these ingredients from bottom to top (the first 5 ingredients).
Then spread on 1/2 cup mayonnaise with 1/2 cup sour cream and sprinkle with the grated cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add the next 4 ingredients and blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture. Mix until well blended.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lace cookies
directions: Beat butter and both sugars well.
Add egg and vanilla, then beat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased sheet, about 6 per sheet.
Bake for 4 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes, then remove carefully.
Sprinkle some with icing sugar.
Grease cookie sheet lightly and bake at 375°.

title: hawaiian barbecue chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in this for 3 to 4 hours, turning every 1/2 to 3/4 of an hour.
Drain before placing on the grill.
Barbecue 3 to 5 minutes over medium heat or until chicken is browned on all sides.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Add to meat in skillet and cook slowly for 15 minutes. Turn meat occasionally in the sauce during cooking time.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook meat until meat is done.
Stir in tomato soup and water. Boil noodles in salt water until done.
Place half of the noodles in casserole.
Next, add layer of meat and then sprinkle with oregano.
Continue with another layer of noodles, meat and oregano.
Put shredded Cheddar or cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: the cake that doesn't last
directions: Measure dry ingredients and sift together.
Dice bananas and measure out 2 cups.
Add bananas to dry ingredients, along with oil, pineapple with juice, vanilla and eggs.
Stir to blend (do not beat).
Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Cut rolls lengthwise; place 6 slices of ham on rolls, 6 slices of cheese and 6 slices of ham again.
Cut rolls.
Melt butter in saucepan; add poppy seed, onion flakes, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
After ingredients are mixed together and warm, spoon over rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix beef with spices listed, then shape into oblong patties. Brown lightly on both sides in oil in skillet.
Remove and place into casserole dish.
Top with onion rings.
In skillet, add flour and water with drippings.
Stir to deglaze.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour gravy over patties.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Scoop pulp from tomatoes (use pulp and juice another time or another way).
Drain and arrange tomatoes in baking dish.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in corn, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley all together.
Spoon corn mixture into tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until heated through.

title: turkey or chicken noodle soup
directions: Put onion, carrots and celery in chicken broth and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Add egg noodles, meat and parsley.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch to water and blend together.
Add this cornstarch mixture to soup and bring back to boil.
Soup is ready to serve as soon as it thickens.

title: spinach chicken salad
directions: Season chicken breasts with lemon pepper, oregano, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Broil until cooked thoroughly; let cool. Slice in thin slices.
Toss spinach and lettuce together with onions and cucumbers.
Add chicken.
Mix olive oil, sugar and balsamic vinegar together.
Shake well and pour over salad.
Add noodles and enjoy!

title: lemon pudding with hot lemon sauce
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add sifted flour and salt, lemon juice and rind.
Beat egg yolks until light; add milk.
Mix well with flour mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites into which has been added 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour into well oiled 2-quart casserole and bake in moderate oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.
If the top crust browns too quickly, put a cookie sheet or aluminum foil over an oven rack above.
Serve hot with Lemon Sauce.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare and bake the cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in thin layers.
Mix together butter, softened cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over cooled cakes.
(The cake is not to be stacked if you have several layers.
Each is individual.)
Cover with drained pineapple.
Cover the pineapple with banana slices.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve.
Keep leftover cake refrigerated.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Saute onion and beef.
Mix chilies into soups with about 1/4 cup milk.
Season with garlic powder and oregano; heat and add olives.
Cut tortillas into quarters.
Pour small amount of soup mix in casserole.
Alternate layers of tortillas, meat and soup mixture.
Add cheese on top.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes until bubbly in 350° oven.
Serves 12.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla; then add all dry ingredients.
Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Add chopped nuts.

title: pickled okra
directions: Grind onions and sweet peppers together.
Use coarse blade. Add salt.
Place in colander to drain; cover with a weight.
Leave for 3 hours.
Set vinegar, sugar and spices in large vessel.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cut stems off okra and add to mixed liquid and ground vegetables.
Heat to almost boil.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Put in jar and seal.
Should set 3 or 4 months before using.

title: peppermint hot chocolate
directions: Directions for candy:
Drop in the candies and stir until dissolved.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Cook spinach in water for a few minutes.
Drain well.
Drain mushrooms.
Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs; turn into greased casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until knife comes clean and crumbs are brown.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Remove bone and skin from salmon.
Put onion and juice of 1/4 to 1/2 lemon in blender.
Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle crushed pecans on top.
Serve with parsley.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon. Mix on medium with mixer until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: holiday butter almond cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg, flour and extract.
Blend thoroughly.
Press with cookie press and bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and apples and let stand while measuring other ingredients.
Bake in shallow pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar free fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add chocolate and stir just until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in Equal and vanilla. Combine chocolate mix with cream cheese and beat until smooth. Stir in nuts and spread mixture in lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: grape-nuts cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand. Do not use an electric mixer. Drop on an ungreased sheet by tablespoon. Flatten a bit with knife dipped in water. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove from baking sheet while still warm.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat the sugar and butter well.
Add the eggs, one at a time. Sift together the flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to butter mixture and beat well. Add the vanilla and pecans.
Spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in sauce in casserole pan, covered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well with an electric beater.
Serve with any crackers.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add powdered sugar, egg and Cool Whip; mix together.
Spread over the cooled pretzel layer.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all together
and put in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 large or about 30 small good for breakfast muffins.

title: dill pickles
directions: Use nice young cucumbers,
cut	either	round
or small whole. Wash cucumbers.
Place a
head
of
dill
in bottom of jar.
Fill jar with cucumbers and add another piece of dill on top of cucumbers.	Drain all
water
from jars.
Mix all other ingredients and bring to a full boil.
Pour over cucumbers and seal airtight.
No processing required.

title: chocolate marshmallow candy
directions: Put all ingredients in double boiler; stir until melted.
Cool slightly and add 2 cups small marshmallows.
Place graham crackers in bottom of a cake pan.
Spread mixture on graham crackers.
Cut into squares after cooled.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Clean shrimp.
Melt enough butter in pan to cover the bottom. Add garlic and saut. Add celery, green pepper and onion.
When these are half cooked, add tomato puree and water.
Add pinch of sugar, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook about 15 minutes.
It should be a nice thick consistency.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: marshmallow fudge bars
directions: Stir together and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Chill and cut into bars.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown onion and pepper in fat.
Add ground chuck, tomato paste, salt, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce and flour.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes; serve on hamburger buns.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand; form small balls.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm and once after cool.
Double recipe to make 9 dozen to 120 cookies.

title: we made ice cream today(easy)
directions: Fill the large bag half full of ice.
Add the salt.
Seal the bag.
Put milk, vanilla and sugar into the small bag.
Seal it. Place the small bag inside the large one and seal again carefully. Shake until mixture is ice cream, about 5 minutes.
Wipe off top of small bag.
Then open carefully and enjoy!

title: monkey dough treats
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Dip buttermilk biscuit quarters in egg and milk mixture, then dip quarters in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Plop in Bundt pan.
Bake at 425°.
Check in 20 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Transfer to baking sheet.
Bake until golden, about 20 minutes.
Make about 6-8 dozen.
Serve hot.

title: spinach-mushroom quiche
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with pie crust.
Cover and refrigerate. In a 12-inch skillet, melt 2 tablespoons margarine.
Saute mushrooms and onion until tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in spinach and set aside.
Preheat oven to 425°.
In small saucepan, melt 1/4 cup margarine.
In medium bowl with wire whisk, beat eggs with cream, milk, flour, salt, pepper, nutmeg and melted butter.
Spoon spinach mixture evenly into crust.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese; pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake 15 minutes. Turn oven to 325°.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: loretta's orange jello supreme
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water; stir in juice.
Add oranges and pineapple; pour into 13 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Let jell.
Whip pudding, milk and Dream Whip.
Pour on top of jelled mixture. Garnish with nuts if desired.

title: pasta and mozzarella salad
directions: Drain cooked macaroni.
Toss with Parmesan Dressing.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Chill.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan over each serving (optional).

title: crab au gratin
directions: Pick through crab to remove all shell.
Mix ingredients and put into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 or 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain and whip with mixer well.
Mix butter, sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla and milk well.
Blend well with potatoes.
Add drained pineapple.
Pour into slightly greased casserole.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out the dough into 12 x 8-inch rectangle on a surface coated with flour.
Place the pepperoni over the dough and top with grated cheese.
Roll up the bread jelly roll fashion.
Place the roll on a pan, seam side down.
Let the dough rise for 1/2 hour, then bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and slice.
Good if dipped in pizza sauce while still warm.

title: baked chicken and dumplings
directions: Salt chicken and put in baking pan.
Melt butter and mix with water and pour over chicken.
Bake until tender.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease. Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl and pour over beef and simmer for 20 min over low heat.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Then combine and sift together flour and all dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin to cream mixture.
Add chocolate chips. Drop by the teaspoonful onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bubble batter #2
directions: Stir; do not shake.
Store in a plastic container.
The longer you store it, the better it gets.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces and roll in 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Melt oleo and other 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over biscuits in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham souffle
directions: Saute mushrooms in oil.
In heavy saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Gradually add broth.
Stir; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add pepper.
Beat yolks in small bowl; add some of hot mixture, whisking constantly.
Return yolk mixture to hot mixture, blending well.
Add mushrooms and ham, salt and pepper.
Set aside; cool 10 minutes.
Cook noodles al dente; drain.
Toss with 2 tablespoons melted butter.

title: flat tires
directions: Partially thaw bread dough; cut each loaf into 6 pieces. Flatten into 5-inch circles.
Combine browned ground beef with sauce.

title: tomato pie
directions: Spread over pie. Bake at 400° for 30-35 minutes.

title: redi-burger loaf
directions: Put into food processor or mash Redi-burger and tofu; blend until it is mixed together.
Place in mixing bowl with the other ingredients.
Mix well with fork or spoon.
Bake in baking dish 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together Russian dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Place chicken in single layer, skin side up, in large shallow baking pan; pour preserves mix on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done, basting occasionally with the pan drippings.
Serve hot with plain rice and the sweet and sour sauce.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 30 minutes, then tear chicken into pieces and layer in bottom of casserole dish.
Add sour cream and cream of chicken over chicken breasts, then sprinkle crumbled crackers on top.
Melt margarine and pour over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes at high speed of electric mixer. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Process in blender on low speed for 30 seconds.
Stir in poppy seed.
Cover and chill.
Stir before serving.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: caramel chews
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in water over low heat.
Top chews with melted chocolate mixture.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: coconut-pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and pineapple.
Add eggs, sifted dry ingredients, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix by hand.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed on box.
Bake on round pizza pan.
Let cool and remove from pan.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar together and spread on baked sugar cookie.
Layer by layer, add fruit:
bananas, pineapple, oranges and strawberries.
Fresh peaches can also be used in place of strawberries.
Mix glaze as directed per box and drizzle over top layer of fruit.
Garnish with kiwi fruit.
Chill for approximately 2 hours before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and continue baking 15 minutes longer.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Leave out enough Cool Whip for top. Add the vanilla wafers and bananas.
Mix together and pour into a large bowl. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Chill.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mound candy
directions: Mix pecans, coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
(This is very hard to mix, may want to use your hands.)
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll in very loose balls (if rolled too hard, they get too hard and are not good.)
These should be about the size of a quarter.
Chill another 2 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice and cook potatoes until just about done.
Then take cream of celery soup and 1/2 soup can milk and put in saucepan. Add cheese, let it melt on stove.
Put potatoes in greased baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Add bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Measure all ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix by hand. Roll out on a well-floured surface, as thin as possible.
Let dry 1 to 2 hours.
Cut in 4 sections.
Roll up 1 section like a scroll.
Thinly slice all sections and fluff with flour.
Spread out noodles and let dry 1 hour.
Drop in boiling water and stir. Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Run under warm water to rinse all flour off.
