title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients to browned beef. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Serve on hamburger buns. This recipe freezes well.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix
in
1/2 quart casserole dish with lid.
Bake in oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until liquid is absorbed at 350°.

title: oklahoma biscuits
directions: Have water just warm enough to melt yeast.
Add salt, sugar and oil to yeast.
Add to flour.
Make biscuits.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Cook.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9 pan, melt butter.
Remove and sprinkle crumbs over batter.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix corn bread, bread crumbs, stuffing mix, onion and half of chopped eggs.
Pour broth over mixture and mix thoroughly.
Place in baking dish.
Spread chicken and rest of eggs over bread mixture. Pour chicken soup over and bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together peanut butter and sugar until crumbly.
Reserve 2 tablespoons.
Put in bottom of a baked pie shell.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Pour into shell.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with reserved peanut butter mixture.
Chill well.

title: stuffed cheese shells
directions: In medium bowl combine eggs, Ricotta, Mozzarella, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons mixture into each shell.
Arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; top with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush cookies in blender; put aside.
Mix cream cheese and oleo until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
In a second bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Stir pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Fry hamburg and drain off any grease.
Cook hamburg, juice, onion and carrots until vegetables are tender.
Add cheese.
Serve after cheese has melted.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar and flour; add whole eggs and beat until fluffy. Add buttermilk, butter and vanilla; mix well. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake for approximately 1 hour or until pie is slightly set. Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza roll-ups
directions: Unroll crescent dough; press perforations together between triangles to form 8 rectangles.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon filling down along side of each rectangle.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, starting with long side.
Cut in half; place, seam side down, on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden, about 15 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put into buttered casserole.
Add crushed corn flakes for topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch mix-ups
directions: Heat butterscotch chips and milk chocolate chips in double boiler until melted.
Add dry roasted peanuts and potato chips. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: henrietta bowen's cornpone
directions: Mix shortening, cornmeal, water and salt in a large saucepan and cook 5 minutes or until thickened.
Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Add milk and blend well.
Add sugar and eggs. Bake at 425° until browned on top.
May double recipe and use a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine sugar, cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine. Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs, 2 sticks melted margarine and vanilla on medium speed of mixer for 10 minutes.
Spread mixture over crust.
Over this, layer bananas, pineapple chunks and Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and chopped nuts.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Melt margarine in skillet; add drained hamburger and onion and mix rest of ingredients into hamburger mix.
Put in long baking dish and cover with cracker crumbs.
Cook in 350° oven until brown.

title: chocolate chip surprise
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Slice and spread half chocolate chip dough in bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese filling. Spread over dough.
Top with remaining cookie dough slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well the corn, flour, sugar and salt.
Add the beaten eggs, margarine and milk.
Bake, covered, 30 to 40 minutes in a pan of hot water at 400°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, celery, green peppers and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
Remove from heat and stir in tomato sauce, water, wine and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Stir in shrimp and bring to a boil, then cover and cook over medium heat for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: lime jello salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add pear juice, plus enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Place pears in the bottom of a mold or bowl.
Place in freezer until set.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump in pineapple. Spread dry cake mix over mixture.
Spread nuts and coconut over cake mix.
Drizzle melted margarine over nuts and coconut.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer at 350°.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Then add all other ingredients and mix well while heating.
In 13 x 9-inch greased pan, layer tortillas, then chicken, then soup mix, then cheese. Repeat layers.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: jollof rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat oil. Add onion and tomatoes and cook until soft. Add tomato sauce, spices, carrots, broth and water. Add rice and simmer on low, stirring occasionally until done.

title: hamburgers
directions: Form patties and brown in butter.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together (melt butter in microwave before adding it).
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour. Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in saucepan; bring to full rolling boil.
Add peanuts slowly so as not to bring boil down.
Cook until peanuts pop; remove from heat and add salt and soda.
Mix well; pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: roasted vidalia onion, cherry tomato and bacon salad
directions: Season the onions with salt and pepper.
Wrap them individually in foil.
Bake them in the middle of a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until they are tender.
Let the onions cool in the foil and discard the foil.
Chop the onions coarse, discarding the root ends.
In a bowl, toss them with the tomatoes, the bacon and the basil or parsley.

title: fools delight
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add egg yolks.
Beat whites separately until stiff and fold into other ingredients.
Add pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Line pan with graham cracker crumbs. Spread mixture on top of crackers.
Put another layer of cracker crumbs on top.
Pour partially congealed jello on top and let set overnight.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Remove stalks and outer leaves of cauliflower.
Separate into flowerets, then soak head down in salted water, 2 tablespoons salt to 1 quart of water, for 1/2 hour.
For a medium-size head, make 1 1/2 cups cream sauce.
Add to this the mace or nutmeg.
Cook cauliflower (do not overcook).
Drain; season.
Grate cheese.
Top with buttered crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or until slightly browned.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Pan fry pork chops.
Salt and pepper and prepare.
Place in a baking pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. You may want to add more juice.

title: egg salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend together cream cheese, mayonnaise, chili sauce, salt and pepper.
Add to egg mixture. Mix well.
Makes 4 cups.
Serve as sandwich filling or mound on lettuce cups for luncheon salad.
Delicious!

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; pour salt over.
Let set for 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Add chopped pepper, celery, onion and carrots.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar, water and celery seed.
Boil 1 minute; let cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.

title: mississippi spice muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix in applesauce and spices.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add to applesauce mixture and beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in lightly greased miniature muffin pans at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Batter keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.
Baked muffins freeze well.
Yield:
84 small muffins.

title: wine cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Turn into oiled tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan when cooled and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: venison bake
directions: In heavy skillet, pour in vegetable oil to heat.
Add carrots and onions.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Remove carrots and onions from skillet.

title: garlicky potato salad
directions: In large pot add potatoes and enough cold water to cover them. Bring to boil over high heat.
Lower heat to medium and boil until tender.
Drain.
In larger bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Add warm potatoes; toss gently to coat.
Let cool to room temperature, tossing occasionally.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Boil raisins in water. Let cool. Save 1 cup juice that raisins were boiled in. Cream butter or shortening with sugar. Add beaten egg yolks to shortening mixture. Add soda and whiskey to raisin juice. Mix with shortening mixture. Add flour, raisins and nuts. Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bacon appetizer crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat the cream cheese, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and milk in small mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles; firmly press perforations together to seal.
Spread each rectangle with 2 rounded measuring tablespoonfuls cream cheese mixture.
Cut each rectangle in half diagonally; repeat with opposite corners.
Cut in half crosswise to form 6 triangles. Fold points over cream cheese mixture.

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Spray a 6-cup shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.

title: mashed potato cocoa cake
directions: Cream butter.
Beat in sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, vanilla, mashed potatoes and cocoa.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, then add nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in buttered flat cake pan for about 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt ingredients over low heat or in crock-pot.
Serve with sliced apples!

title: holiday wreaths
directions: Melt butter in microwave for 30 seconds. Add marshmallows and coat with butter. Microwave for 1 minute, stir and microwave for 1 minute longer. Add food coloring and vanilla; stir. Fold in cornflakes and blend well. Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Shape into wreaths with fingers. Decorate with red hots. Refrigerate until set.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Beat eggs; add flour, milk and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add spinach, cheese and onion; fold in.
Pour in pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Remove and cool 45 minutes to set.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Makes 38 to 45 pieces.

title: jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in oblong lightly greased baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix together the applesauce and the soda.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Soak raisins in warm water, then drain real good.
Mix together and add raisins dredged with flour.
Add nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: bacon cheese sauce
directions: Saute onion with bacon until desired doneness.
Drain off fat. Make cream sauce with flour, milk and cheese.
Add pepper when sauce is desired consistency.
Add eggs; beat into sauce.
Great on spaghetti.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Place meat in shallow pan.
Pour marinade over and refrigerate 3 hours.
Remove meat from marinade and cut into 1/2 x 3-inch strips.
Melt margarine in 1 large skillet.
Add onions, peppers and seasoning salt; saute until tender.
Place meat into large cast-iron skillet and sear over medium heat until browned.
Add vegetables.
Place tomatoes over both meat and vegetables.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serves 6.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix according to directions on box and bake in 3 cake pans.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup and sour cream in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Spoon stuffing over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbling.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for pecans.
Pour into small casserole.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Use Fritos to dip.

title: make-ahead scrambled eggs
directions: In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add flour; cook and stir until the mixture begins to bubble. Gradually stir in milk; bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Stir in the cheese until melted; set aside. In a large skillet, saute mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until tender. Add eggs and salt; cook and stir until the eggs are completely set. Add the cheese sauce and broccoli; mix well. Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: tomato-zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread mustard evenly over pie shell and cover with Mozzarella.
Make layered overlapping of tomato and zucchini slices alternating for color.
Sprinkle half of garlic, oregano, salt and pepper and drizzle half of olive oil over layer of tomatoes and zucchini.
Make second layer of tomatoes and zucchini and sprinkle with rest of garlic, oregano, salt and pepper and drizzle remaining olive oil on top.
Put pie on baking sheet and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped basil and serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk.
Sift dry ingredients into another bowl and blend in onion.
Combine dry ingredients with milk mixture. Drop into hot fat (370°).
Fry until deep brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white with 1 tablespoon of water until frothy, but not stiff.
Mix pecans in egg white mixture thoroughly.
Mix dry ingredients and pour over pecans.
Coat throughly.
Place on a cookie sheet in a single layer and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour, stirring at the 15 minute interval.
Place on waxed paper in single layer until cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large shallow dish; set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables, tossing lightly.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours. Drain and serve in a lettuce lined bowl.
Yields 6 servings.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water and juice.
Add 2 cups of cold water and ice.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Add cherries and pineapple.
Chill. Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening; add eggs, one at a time.
Add sugar gradually.
Combine baking powder with flour and add alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add bacon, margarine, egg and orange juice.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by level tablespoons 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° or until edges are lightly browned but cookies are still soft.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken (or turkey) tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
While spaghetti is boiling, saute mushrooms in separate pan.
Add wine.
Drain spaghetti and add mushrooms.
In separate saucepan, make a sauce of butter, flour and chicken broth.
Remove from heat and add heated whipping cream.
Add shredded chicken and sauce to spaghetti-mushroom mixture.
Mix well.
Place in greased baking dish and sprinkle the top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven until lightly browned and heated through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and top with prepared Stove Top dressing.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon chicken bake
directions: Place chicken
in
a
10 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish with one inch of lemon juice in the bottom of the dish.
Baste with sauce. Bake
covered
at
for
30 minutes.
Remove from oven; baste
with
sauce.
Bake,	uncovered, for	15
minutes longer or until brown and tender.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: mama's strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, together and bake at 350 degrees for 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: escalloped eggplant(original morrison recipe)
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Boil until soft and drain.
Saute onion in margarine and add to eggplant.
Mix 2/3 of cracker crumbs with eggplant.
Blend egg with milk.
Add to eggplant mixture. Add bacon drippings, salt and pepper to taste.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs and brown in moderate 350° oven.

title: york family dinner rolls
directions: Stir yeast into warm water.
Add sugar, cooled milk, salt, egg, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in enough flour (about 1 1/2 cups) to make dough handle easily. Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with cloth.
Let rest until doubled. Punch down and shape into rolls; let rise, covered.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on greased sheet.

title: microwave candy
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips together for 3 or 4 minutes on High.
Stir in the nuts and potato chips.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.

title: mostaccioli chili casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain; add the chili and heat until melted. Saute onions and garlic; add to meat.
Add rest of ingredients. Cook pasta and drain, then add to meat mixture.
Put in large casserole or 2 medium.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 1/2 hour.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat cream cheese, soup and onions until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add mayonnaise.
Dissolve gelatin and water over heat.
Add to soup mixture.
Add shrimp and celery.
Pour into mold.
Chill 12 hours.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: campbelled eggs
directions: In skillet, fry bacon until crisp. Remove and crumble. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Cook peppers and onions in drippings until tender.

title: fiesta banana cake
directions: Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: clara archer's creole tuna(camp blanding, florida 1945)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add green peppers; cook 3 minutes. Stir in flour; add milk gradually.
When smooth, add tomatoes, mushrooms and seasoning.
Cook until thickened; stir constantly. After 15 minutes, add the tuna.
Cool 2 minutes.
Serve over toast. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: eggplant
directions: Mix eggplant, onion, peppers, salt and pepper in saucepan. Cover with water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add tomato and chili powder. Simmer until tender.
Add crumbled biscuits, enough to thicken. Stir constantly.

title: brandied fruit cake (30 days)
directions: Combine starter juice, peaches (with juice) and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir daily for 10 days.
On the 10th day add 2 1/2 cups sugar and pineapple chunks with juice.
Stir daily for 10 days.
On the 20th day, add 2 1/2 cups sugar and maraschino cherries.
Stir daily for 10 days.
On the 30th day, make cakes.
Makes 3 cakes.

title: pumpkin pie squares(finger food)
directions: Mix until crumbly and press lightly into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Pour strawberries into mixture.
Pour into cooked pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip. Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger and bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Brown ground meat with chopped onion and drain well.
In large Pyrex bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Add ground meat and crumbled bacon.
Cover and must let it sit in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: mexicali rice
directions: Cook onions and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until golden brown. Add ground beef and other ingredients and simmer until hot.
Serve over corn chips.
Garnish with grated sharp Cheddar cheese, chopped ripe olives and chopped avocados.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: good baked beans
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Umm Umm Good!

title: stove top tuna casserole
directions: Boil macaroni 10 minutes.
Drain off water over peas and mushrooms in a strainer.
Heat mushroom soup and combine with macaroni, peas and mushrooms.
Add the cheese from package and tuna.
Serve with French bread.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and mix lightly.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: two-crust lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch and the 1/4 cup water in a 3-quart saucepan. Add boiling water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute until thickened. Stir in sugar, lemon rind and butter; cool. Stir in eggs and lemon juice. Pour mixture into a 9-inch pastry lined plate.

Roll out remaining pastry, cut slits for steam to escape. Adjust over filling; flute to make stand up edge. Brush top with 1 tablespoon milk. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes, then at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden.

title: mother's salmon croquettes
directions: Put salmon in large bowl.
Remove all bones.
Add egg and meal.
Mix well.
Put shortening in skillet and let it melt while mixing the salmon.
Form patties (will make 12 small or 8 large). Fry golden brown on each side at medium heat.
Drain on a paper towel before serving.

title: pasta caesar salad
directions: Add a little of the salad dressing to cooked noodles, then remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Just before serving, toss with the remaining salad dressing.

title: simple and good cookies
directions: Mix ingredients until moistened.
Use a spoonful of dough and press dough lightly on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rich and charlie's salad
directions: Mix well; chill well and toss with dressing just before ready to serve.

title: cranberry-orange muffins
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic in skillet; put in crock-pot with all other ingredients, except beans.
Cook on low setting 8 to 10 hours.
Add beans last hour.
Serve over Fritos or rice.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass bowl. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Take out of microwave and stir.
Cook on High for 30 seconds to 1 minute until light brown in color.
Stir in butter, vanilla and baking soda.
Will be light and foamy.
Spread out on margarine covered cookie sheet.
Let cool.
When hard, break into pieces.

title: tostado soup
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain well. Puree tomatoes. Add to pot along with beans, water, picante sauce & cumin. Simmer for 10 minutes. Ladle into soup bowls & top with slightly crumbled corn chips, and
cheese.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add milk and egg.
Add dry ingredients. Add chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tangy turnips
directions: Place turnips in a saucepan; cover with water.
Add salt, and bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, or until turnips are tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: **apricot-pineapple dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in one cup boiling water.
Add sugar, salt, apricots and pineapple with juice (3/4 cup).
Cool until thickens. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9-inch square pan with half the cake, broken in small pieces. Pour over half fruit jello mixture.
Then another layer of cake pieces and another layer of mixture.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares.
Serves 16.

title: italian dressing for veggies
directions: Mix together and let set for about 1 to 2 hours.

title: heavenly dream cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Boil sugar and pineapple for 5 minutes.
Pour the mixture over hot baked cake that has been pierced with a fork.
Let cake and pineapple mixture cool.
Mix dry pudding mixture with 1/2 Cool Whip and pour over cake.
Add bananas and cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut over bananas and top with chopped nuts and cherries.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, corn flakes, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and onion.
Mix well.
Form small balls and put in pan larger than 9 x 13-inch.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to box directions.
Add Eagle Brand milk and bananas, then add Cool Whip.
Layer a cake dish with wafers and then pudding and then repeat.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions into small pieces.
In a large pot, mix vinegar and sugar and bring to a boil and cook for approximately 15 minutes or until onions appear clear.
Spoon into sterilized jars and seal.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and miniature marshmallows.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Add pineapple, nuts and whipping cream.
Mix well and place in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix well, except for cornmeal.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix self-rising cornmeal (about 3 cups) and pour on top. Bake at 450° for 45 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: caramel crispy treats
directions: Melt caramels with margarine and water in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Pour over cereal; toss until well coated.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Let stand until firm.

title: pineapple delight salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook about 10 minutes or until it thickens.
Let cool; line dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Alternate layers of crumbs and sauce until dish is filled.

title: "quick and easy" sweet and sour chicken
directions: Saute chicken in oil until lightly browned.
Add garlic, onion, pepper strips and carrots.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add bouillon, teriyaki sauce, vinegar, sugar and pineapple with juice. Bring to a full boil.

title: seven week muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt with milk and beat on "stir" with mixer.
Add rest of ingredients and beat again.
Line muffin pans with paper liners.
Fill each about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Place ground chuck in center of aluminum pie pan.
Put onion, potatoes, carrot, bell pepper on and around ground chuck.
Cover with foil; cook in oven for 40 minutes at 400°.
Unwrap; eat from pie pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add barbecue sauce, if desired.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix buttermilk, oil and eggs. Stir two mixtures together.
Will keep in refrigerator 1 month. Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn and milk, gradually stir in egg.
Add the rest of the ingredients and a dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs over the top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry dessert or blueberry dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, oleo and sugar together.
Pat this on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: raisin meringue pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar and flour.
Stir in sour cream, egg yolks, spices and salt until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in raisins; cover and set aside.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add berries and mix gently.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add pecans or walnuts and mix.
Pour 1/2 of gelatin mixture into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or jello mold.
Chill slightly.
Fold sour cream into remaining gelatin mixture.
Pour carefully into mold and chill until set.

title: kraut salad
directions: Put sugar, oil and vinegar in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour over ingredients.
Put in refrigerator.
Keeps for weeks.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Pare rind and all pink edges from watermelon and cut into squares or fancy shapes.
(Choose melon with thick, firm rind. Trim off outer green skin and all pink flesh so only the thick white part of rind remains.)
Cover with brine made by mixing salt with 3 quarts cold water.
Add ice cubes.
Let stand 5 to 6 hours in crock or other thick glass container (no metal ones).
Drain. Rinse in cold water.
Cover with cold water and cook until fork-tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Don't overcook!
Drain. Combine sugar with vinegar, water and spices tied loosely in cloth bag.
Add red or green coloring if desired.
Boil 5 minutes and pour over watermelon with spices.
Add lemon slices if desired. Let stand overnight (covered and room temperature).
Heat to boiling.
Cook until rind is translucent and hot throughout (10 minutes); pack in hot, sterile jars.
Add 1 stick of cinnamon from bag to each jar.
Cover with boiling syrup to top of jars.
Wipe with dry towel.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Combine last 6 ingredients.
Add chicken breasts.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Grill over hot coals.
Serves 12.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix
together all ingredients except pork chops.
Place chops in
x 13-inch pan.
Pour liquid over chops.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: quick unusual corn bread
directions: Saute the onion in the melted butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Remove the onions.
Combine the corn muffin mix, egg, milk and corn to make a soft batter.

title: homemade pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheeses...add pimento.
Add mayo mixture to taste.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Blend sugar, milk, oleo and vanilla.
Melt wax and chocolate chips together.
Pinch off sugar mixture; wrap cherries and dip into chocolate mixture.
Let stand 7 to 10 days for center to get runny.

title: mexican beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in a big baking dish and bake at 350° for about an hour.
Stir a couple of times while they're baking.

title: fresh strawberry spread(diabetic)
directions: Wash and clean berries; discard hulls.
Measure 3 cups.
Cut in small, bite size pieces and place in a heavy pan with 2 tablespoons of cold water and lemon juice.
Partially crush berries; bring to a boil.
Stir and cook rapidly about 5 minutes until berries are cooked.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter in a small bowl with vanilla and the sugars until fluffy-light; beat in egg yolk.
Stir together flour and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Form into small balls, about a teaspoon of batter in each, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork dipped in flour; top with a pecan half.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Cool on rack.
Yield:
3 to 4 dozen.

title: lemon cake
directions: Grease cake pan and flour.
Mix the first 4 ingredients and bake at 350° for 33 to 38 minutes.
Take from oven and make lots of holes with a fork all the way to the bottom of the pan.
Mix together the lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Spoon over cake. Cover with Cool Whip or sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: wisconsin cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender; drain.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in flour; cook and stir 2 or 3 minutes until bubbly.
Stir in soda.
Gradually add milk and broth.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, stirring, until mixture thickens slightly, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cheese and red pepper; stir until melted.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix mincemeat, soda, eggs, shortening, sugar and water.
Mix in flour.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonful.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, combine all but sausage.
Bring to boil and cook until tender.
While the soup mixture is getting hot, brown sausage and add sausage and drippings to soup.

title: shirley's chocolate goop
directions: In heavy pan, melt butter and chocolate together. Add sugar and stir well. Add milk slowly while stirring, then bring to a slow boil. Simmer 2 or 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Serve hot over ice cream or as a topping on yummy desserts. Store in the refrigerator. Heat briefly in microwave.

title: lemon or lime salad
directions: Make Jell-O in casserole dish and refrigerate until set. Drain pineapple and save juice.
Dissolve cream cheese in juice from crushed pineapple.
Whip Jell-O and add evaporated milk until Jell-O and milk are well mixed.
Fold in crushed pineapple and cream cheese and juice mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to instructions on bag.
Drain and spoon into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Set aside.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Follow directions on cornbread mix box.
Add the extra egg and chopped bacon, onions, cheese, pepper and corn.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in iron skillet while oven is preheating.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Soften cream cheese; add 2 whole eggs and whip until creamy. Add sugar, vanilla and almond and whip until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake 20 minutes.
If frozen strawberries are to be used, thaw, then thicken with Jell-O and water.
After this begins to thicken, add to cream cheese mixture.
After this thickens put whipped cream on top.

title: fire and ice
directions: Spread on Triscuits and put under the broiler until bubbling. Can be made and kept for weeks in the refrigerator.
Makes a lot. Terrific spread on rye bread and broiled for an open face sandwich.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: double deck cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to pineapple syrup to make 1 3/4 cups.
Make cherry jello as directed on box, chill until partially set and add tidbits.
Pour into oiled 8-inch square pan, chill until firm.
Soften cheese and heat with cream.
Spread over cherry jello.
Chill.

title: kounoupidi me tiri (cauliflower in cheese sauce)
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets and cook in boiling, salted water until tender; drain and arrange in shallow baking dish.
Melt butter; add flour and stir over high heat until browned slightly.
Add milk and cook, stirring until thickened. Add cheese and cook, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add the hot mixture gradually to the eggs while continuing to beat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour over cauliflower and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: candy bar brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix according to package directions.
Place 1 box of batter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break candy bars into squares.
Lay squares on brownie mix in tiled fashion.
Cover with second brownie mix batter.
Bake at 300°.
Let them cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: greek sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Do not brown hamburg.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or more.
Salt to suit.

title: frosted banana bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bars test done.
Very good.

title: 4-layer chocolate pie
directions: Melt the margarine in Pyrex casserole. Add the cracker crumbs. Press into crust around bottom of casserole.
Let cool.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar and lemon juice in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Stir in gelatin.
Ladle into hot sterilized 8 ounce jars.
Yield: 3 or 4 jars.

title: sweet potato souffl
directions: Boil yams in water until tender. Remove from water; peel and mash in mixing bowl. Add butter, eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt. Beat with mixer for a minute. Pour into well-greased casserole. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. When firm and lightly crusty, it is done.

title: spring peach-pear dream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and preserves in bowl.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust.
Arrange fruit attractively on top.

title: chicken milano
directions: Saute butter, onion, garlic and mushrooms in saucepan.
Slice or dice the squash.
Add chicken to saucepan and stir in undiluted tomato soup.
Add remaining ingredients except rice or pasta. Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together sugar, oleo and crushed pretzels.
Put in an 8 x 10-inch pan and bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove stems, seeds, etc. from peppers.
Boil in salt water for 5 minutes. Drain and rub inside of peppers with salt. Stuff with ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
When cooked, sprinkle with more cheese.

title: kids favorite biscuits
directions: Separate biscuits; pat into bottom and up the sides of a greased muffin pan.
In a small bowl, combine peanut butter and jelly until smooth; place a rounded tablespoon into each biscuit cup.
Bake at 450 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 7-layer bean dip
directions: In a glass baking dish layer all ingredients as listed from the top.
Start with the beans and end with the cheese. Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Scrub but do not peel zucchini; trim ends.
Cut the zucchini into 2-inch lengths, then cut each length into quarters, lengthwise.
Bring zucchini to a boil in salted water to cover; simmer until tender, but not soft.
Drain thoroughly.
Butter a 9-inch ovenproof dish; arrange zucchini in a layer over the bottom.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika and cheese.
Pour the melted butter over all.
Place under the broiler until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy creamy broccoli soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook onions in margarine until tender. Add milk and cream cheese; stir over medium heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly. Stir occasionally.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat
egg
whites,
baking powder and salt until thick. Beat in
sugar
until
meringue
holds peaks.
Add pecans and crackers. Pour
into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool and cover with whipped cream before serving.

title: ground beef savaries
directions: Combine all but crackers and last items. Shape into 30 (1-inch) balls. Flatten slightly. Place on cracker. Make a hollow. Fill with catsup, mustard or cheese. Place crackers on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put in pie dish.
Put a layer of sour cream, chopped tomatoes, peppers and onions on top for decoration.
Serve with corn chips.

title: sweet lime pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in lime and water for 24 hours.
Drain and soak in fresh water for 3 hours. Drain.
Heat and pour over well drained pickles,
the sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, pickling spices and allspice.
Soak 24 hours.
Boil all ingredients for 35 minutes. Can, hot, in sterilized jars.

title: good casserole(a meal in itself)
directions: I cook this all together until potatoes are tender, adding the rice last as Minute rice.
Add 2 cans of cream of chicken soup. Pour in baking dish and cover with dressing (or I use corn chips, corn bread crumbs or anything your family likes).

title: nappa salad
directions: Saute sesame seed, almonds, noodles and oleo until lightly brown; cool and put on salad.
Chop cabbage and onions.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put green beans, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup in casserole pan.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Then add onion rings and cook for about 5 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover with foil and freeze.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush oreo cookies.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix well with cookies.
Put one half of mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Add cool whip.
Put one half mixture on top of crushed cookies.
Mix chocolate instant pudding according to instructions on box.
Pour on top of cream cheese layer.
Layer remaining cream cheese mixture on top.
Top with remaining cookies.
Chill one hour.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes until chunky. Blend butter, sour cream, mayonnaise, chives, bacon, salt and pepper.
Toss potatoes in the mixture.
Put potatoes into a dish. Stir in most of the grated cheese (leave some to put on top).
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: green onion wraps
directions: Clean and cut green onions 6-inches or so.
Soften cream cheese.
Apply to meat slices.
Roll around onion to keep closed; dab cream cheese at end of meat wrap!

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet, lightly greased.
Bake according to package until lightly browned; cool.
Spread Ranch dressing on top.
Other spreads may be used (cream cheese and sour cream.)
Sprinkle vegetables and cheese on top.
Cut and serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry chopped onion in small pieces, then add 1 1/2 cups rice, 2 quarts of water and tomatoes; salt and pepper to taste.
More water can be added.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend pudding and milk with electric mixer on low. Fold in cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Crush cookies as small as possible. Make alternate layers starting with cookies.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Put in plastic flowerpot. Top with plastic flower and spade.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Cook asparagus in rapidly boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain and rinse with cold water until asparagus is cold.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese, then add marshmallow cream and beat until smooth.
(You could add a drop of red food coloring for color.) Serve with cut-up fresh fruit.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cook beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.
Stir baking mix and water in baking dish until moistened; spread evenly.
Spread beef mixture over batter; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
High altitude no changes.

title: greek salad
directions: Score cucumber by running tines of fork lengthwise down sides; slice.
Toss cucumber with remaining ingredients.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup of water (add the rest if needed), baking powder and salt until well blended.
Knead for 1 minute.
Cover bowl and let rise for 16 to 20 minutes.
Pat bread out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut in wedges.
With knife, make 1-inch slice in the middle of each wedge.
Heat oil (1 1/2-inches) in large skillet and fry wedges until golden brown.
Serve with butter, honey or jelly.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients; mix well with hands and shape into a ball.
Refrigerate cheese ball for 5 minutes; then garnish with the parsley, olives or chopped pecans (or a combination of all three).

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large skillet, cook onions in butter until lightly browned. In crock-pot, combine browned onions in butter with bouillon, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Serve with warm French bread.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Add milk. Mix cocoa with other 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix all together and beat well.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into deep unbaked pie crust.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french toast in a bowl
directions: Pour melted butter over bread cubes to coat.
Mix Egg Beaters, milk, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and bananas (if used) and pour over bread cubes and stir gently to coat.
Bake in greased 2 quart baking dish, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes, or until a knife comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Dish into bowls that have been coated or drizzled with maple syrup.

title: butterscotch icing
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter.
Add milk.
Boil 2 minutes; chill. In mixer add 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar more or less desired; spread.

title: president george bush's pralines
directions: Cover 2 cookie sheets with waxed paper; set aside.
Use a wooden spoon to mix brown sugar and milk in a 2-quart glass container.
Stir well to make sure there are no lumps which tend to burn during microwaving.
Add pecans.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes; stir.
Then microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until the mixture reaches 240° on a candy thermometer (the soft ball stage). To test, drip some candy mixture into a cup of ice water.
It should form a soft ball when pressed between the fingers.
Use the wooden spoon to beat the mixture about 3 minutes or until it begins to thicken slightly.
Quickly drop mixture by tablespoonfuls onto the prepared waxed paper, making sure that each praline includes about 3 pecan halves.
Let harden completely before pulling off paper.
Store them in an airtight container.
Yields 24 pralines, 110 calories each.

title: chicken whip
directions: Clean the chicken breasts, then rub down with Miracle Whip. Season with salt, pepper and Mrs. Dash. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.
It's best flavor comes out when grilled but also great in the oven.

title: turkey scaloppini
directions: Coat cutlets with flour. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add half of cutlets; cook on each side for 1 to 2 minutes or until no longer pink. Remove from skillet. Repeat with remaining olive oil and cutlets. Add water, chicken broth, butter, garlic, sage and bouillon to skillet. Bring to a boil; cook for 1 to 2 minutes. Add cutlets to skillet; reduce heat to low and cook, stirring and turning cutlets over to coat for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: low-fat zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add cheese.
Cook the flour, butter, sugar and eggs until thick.
Let cool, then mix in pineapple, cheese and marshmallows.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and salt together until soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.

title: pineapple cream meringue pie
directions: Drain crushed pineapple.
Mix together in bowl the sugar, salt, flour and egg yolks.
Put milk in pan; mix in sugar flour mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Be careful not to scorch.
Remove from stove and cool.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Put into pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from egg whites.

title: chicken broccoli vegetables
directions: In skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot oleo, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Remove chicken.
In same skillet, add remaining oleo.
Cook broccoli, carrots and mushrooms for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low, simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato bake
directions: Spray "Pam" in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add hash browns.
Drizzle in melted butter.
Mix cheese, sour cream and chicken soup; spread over potatoes.
Crush corn flakes or potato chips and put over potatoes.
Drizzle with more butter.
(Durkee onion rings can also be used as topping.) Bake 1 hour and 35 minutes at 375°.

title: venison roast
directions: Make 4 or 5 slits in top of roast and insert garlic cloves (1/4) in each.
Pour vinegar over the top and sprinkle with crushed marjoram.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours.
During last half hour, pour soup over top.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix the hamburger, onion, bread, egg, milk, salt and pepper. Make into meatballs.
Fry in 1/4 cup of oil until done.
Remove meatballs and put soup and milk into frying pan; heat.
Add meatballs and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: mrs. lambooy's layered salad
directions: Place vegetables and bacon in 9 x 13-inch pan in layers.
Mix mayonnaise with cheese and sugar to taste.
Spread mayo mixture on top of vegetables.
Chill.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Delicious served with ham.

title: korean salad
directions: Prepare in advance. Mix together oil, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and onion. Set aside.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to become room temperature.
With your hands moistened, blend the dressing into the cream cheese.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Chill completely and serve with crackers.

title: potato casserole supreme
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender. Drain and beat in large bowl of electric mixer until fluffy, adding butter, seasonings and milk.
Turn into buttered casserole dish. Fold cheese into whipping cream and spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no bake squares
directions: Add custard mixture to crumb mixture.
Mix well; press into pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine egg, water and vanilla.
Set aside. Blend brown sugar and oil in large bowl at low speed.
Add egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture; stir until smooth. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cook on sheets for 1 minute. Remove to cooling racks.
One cookie contains 80 calories, 2 grams fat and 1 gram saturated fat.

title: key lime pie
directions: 1. Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine, 1 teaspoon sweetener in 7-inch spring form pan; pat evenly on bottom and 1/2 inch up side of pan.

title: cheese roll
directions: Flatten Velveeta with hands between sheets of wax or parchment paper or plastic wrap.
Roll with a rolling pin until Velveeta is in a rectangle of 16 x 18 and fairly thin. Spread cream cheese on flattened Velveeta.
Top cream cheese evenly with chilies, olives and green onions.
Peel off bottom paper as you roll cheese "jelly roll" style.
Serve with crackers.
Can put salsa over top.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix apples, cranberries, white sugar and water together and place in a greased casserole dish (6 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch). Mix melted butter, oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and pecans.
Put this on top of apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: egg - cheese casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl. Tear bread into eggs.
Add milk, mustard, cheese and salt.
Add sausage.
Place in a 9 x 13 inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate over-night.
Let stand 15 minutes before baking.
Bake in a 350 degree oven 45 minutes or until brown.

title: tuna cheddar sandwich loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, sprinkle yeast over water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add sugar, butter, milk and egg; blend.
Add 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt and beat vigorously.
Gradually add rest of flour to form a stiff dough.

title: creamy dijon green beans
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, melt margarine over medium-high heat; add flour and stir quickly to combine.
Continuing to stir, gradually add milk.
Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except green beans.
Arrange green beans in serving bowl; add sour cream mixture and stir to coat.

title: bubble bread
directions: Place frozen rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and add pudding mix, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls and let rise overnight on counter.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Turn out on serving platter.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Add 3 quarts ginger ale when served.
Makes 2 gallons without ginger ale.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into 6 oval patties.
Place on broiler rack.

title: neiman-marcus oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
In a medium size bowl, mix together the flour and baking powder.
In a large bowl using a mixer at medium speed, blend together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg.
On low speed, blend in flour mixture, oats and peel.
Stir in raisins.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto prepared baking sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Scald milk.
Put eggs in a bowl; beat just until the whites and yolks are mixed.
Add the sugar, salt and nutmeg; stir until blended.
Gradually stir the hot milk into the egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into 6 custard cups; put in baking pan with 1 inch of hot water.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until done.
Remove cups from hot water to cool.
Makes 6 servings.

title: granny hughe's boiled custard
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring often.

title: cheese cake
directions: Heat and cool the pineapple and sugar.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Soft set and whip.
Mix cracker crumbs, margarine and powdered sugar.
Set aside 1 cup.
Press in large rectangle dish.
Mix milk and cream cheese.
Mix with jello.
Pour on top of crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.

title: texas style meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cook at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Before the 2 hours are up, add tortilla chips and cheese on top. Put in broiler for about 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Velveeta or Monterey Jack is best.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust; crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine oleo, pretzels and 1/3 cup of the sugar.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake approximately 6 minutes.
Cool. Break into small pieces and place in plastic bag until ready to serve.
Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup of the sugar and pineapple. Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Just before serving, add pretzel mixture to cheese mixture.
A good recipe to make the day before serving.

title: green chili
directions: Cut meat in bite size pieces and cut off fat on meat.
Brown in a skillet.
Place all ingredients in a crock-pot on low all day or in a Dutch oven on top of stove.
Cook until meat is tender.

title: crab cakes
directions: In large pot, melt butter and cream cheese.
Add crabmeat and coat well with cream cheese mixture.
Warm.
Put on toasted English muffins.

title: rice cream mold
directions: Eight ounces Cool Whip will work for whipping cream.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Blend in gravy mix, garlic salt, water and rice.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add frozen peas.
Continue to simmer until rice is tender.
Stir in 3/4 can of onion rings.
Sprinkle remainder on top of the casserole before serving.

title: baked cream cheese appetizer
directions: Sprinkle and gently press minced dill weed on top of cream cheese.
Place cream cheese, dill side down, in center of crescent rolls.
Bring side up snugly around cheese, pinching to seal.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp and mash with a fork.
Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Add to shrimp.
Add all other ingredients.
Add salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire to taste.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Place the oil and butter in a shallow cooking pan (a jelly roll pan is perfect) and put in a preheated 375° oven to melt. Set aside.

title: venison roast
directions: Place roast in center of cooking bag.
Cut potatoes and carrots into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices.
Dice celery and arrange around the roast.
Tie roasting bag.
Place in the center of the oven.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dip
meat
in
flour and brown in hot fat.
Add onions, garlic and
mushrooms.
Combine soup, sour cream, liquid from mushrooms and
seasonings.
Pour
over
meat and simmer until tender (about 1 hour).
Serve over hot rice or spaghetti.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Liquify in blender and pour into graham cracker pie shell. Bake 1/2 hour at 350° until slightly golden.
Top with favorite filling, if desired.

title: squash fritters
directions: Beat egg; add squash, then add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonful into deep fat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas in a large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs well in a small bowl and add to bananas.
Mix well.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla, cake mix and nuts.
Mix well.
Divide into three 5 x 9 inch loaf pans and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Do not over cook!

title: pork loin roast with apple glaze
directions: Rub roast with mixture of flour, mustard, salt and pepper. Roast 35 to 40 minutes to the pound at 350°.
About an hour before roast is done, spread with apple glaze made by combining remaining ingredients.
Return to oven until meat is done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In a small skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Simmer onion, pepper and mushrooms, stirring until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir together with next 6 ingredients.
Add noodles, mixing well.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.
You should use Hellmann's only.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in water for 10 minutes.
Pour water off.
Chop broccoli.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add 7-Up.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked apple square
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Add oil and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 4 to 8 hours.
Serve warm from crock-pot. Makes about 12 cups.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix milk, melted margarine, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add chopped pecans and coconut.
Mix well.
Make into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin; dip balls.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together but flour and soda.
Bring to a boil.
Cool to room temperature, then add flour and soda.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° either in loaf pan, 9 x13-inch or in 2 layers.

title: grilled pork chop sauce
directions: Heat and stir until mixed thoroughly.
Brush on pork chops. Grill pork chops while continuing to add more sauce.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain Shoe Peg corn. Mix all together; chill.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Saute shrimp, but do not over cook.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, garlic salt, onion, Italian seasoning and Tabasco, if desired.
Add shrimp; chill and serve.

title: italian mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy medium saucepan over medium-low heat. Add mushrooms and onion; cook until onion is translucent, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste.
Add stock and vermouth; simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Degrease soup, if necessary.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately, passing Parmesan cheese separately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Toss bread and pineapple in a bowl. Spread out in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In the same bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy. Beat in sugar and butter until blended.
Pour over bread mixture.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes until puffed and golden brown.
Serve at once.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Blend in next 5 ingredients.
Add 1 1/2 c. raisins if desired.
Chill.
Roll dough into small balls. Dip in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Cover rice with water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, bring milk and sugar to a boil in saucepan.
Add rice and water. Stir and return mixture to a boil.
Reduce to simmer.
Simmer 45 to 50 minutes, stirring frequently.
Watch carefully as it has a tendency to boil over when not stirred every few minutes.
Simmer to just about the thickness you want pudding to be.
Remove from heat.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: 1. Heat oven to moderate - 350 degrees.
Crease cookie sheet. 2. Beat brown sugar and granulated sugar, shortening, egg, vanilla, and milk until smooth.

title: blueberry-cream cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter baking dish.
Mix crumbs, powdered sugar and butter in medium bowl.
Press into bottom of baking dish.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and eggs in medium bowl until smooth.
Spread over crust.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool.
Stir lemon juice into pie filling and spread over cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: tropical fruit sundaes
directions: Combine banana and lemon juice; stir in marmalade and preserves.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated through. Remove from heat; stir in rum flavoring.
Spoon over ice cream. Sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: ruth lyons' wine jelly
directions: Mix wine and sugar in top part of double boiler.
Place over boiling water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat. Stir in Certo (and food coloring, if desired) immediately.
Pour into jelly glasses.
Cover with 1/8-inch melted paraffin.
Cover with lids when cool.

title: berries and dumplings
directions: Wash berries and combine with water and sugar, using a kettle with lid.
Boil until berries are soft and there is lots of juice. Mix biscuit mix with milk.
Drop by teaspoonful in boiling berries.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Sugar and cinnamon may be added to dumpling mix for sweeter dough.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in liquids and mix, making a stiff batter.
Do not knead at this time.
Oil another bowl, put dough in bowl and turn over so it will be on top and bottom.
Cover with foil and let stand overnight on counter (if house is cool, set in oven to rise).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add water, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat in pumpkin.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour in 4 (1 pound) coffee cans (greased and floured) 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Roll each in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar, eggs and other ingredients.
Roll into two rolls and let stand on wax paper in refrigerator.
Cut into slices, 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, depending on size of cookie.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, salt, pepper and garlic salt together.
Pat chicken dry and coat well in sour cream mixture.
Roll in stuffing mix and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 stick butter over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken and pour other 1/2 butter over chicken and bake 15 minutes more.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients together and mix.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls the size of walnut.
Dip in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Process beef.
Keep 1 cup to roll in.
Mix all other ingredients together and chill.
Shape.
Roll in beef and then serve.
Keep refrigerated until all used.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat.
Add roux, onion, celery, carrots, package of stew mix and water.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes.
Lower heat and cook for 1/2 hour.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together cocoa, flour, soda and baking powder.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, mix together sugars, eggs, lard or Crisco and milk.
Add cocoa mixture; blend well.
Add vanilla and hot water.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caraway cheese treat
directions: Combine yeast and water in a large bowl.
Combine sugar, margarine, salt and milk; heat slightly.
Cool to lukewarm. Add eggs, caraway seed, celery seed and cheese.
Add flour to make stiff dough, kneading dough thoroughly.
Let rise until double. Work down the dough. Roll out and divide into 4 strips.
Twist two together. Seal ends. Place in greased loaf pan and let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sherbet.
Refrigerate. Add sherbet immediately before serving.
Serves about 25 people.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar together.
Add carrots and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Add nuts last.
Put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry. Cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter and oil together.
Stir in eggs and flavorings along with dry ingredients.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Add chicken, coating well. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Remove chicken from sauce. Roll in mixed crumbs.
Arrange in shallow pan.
Melt margarine; spoon half over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Spoon rest of margarine over chicken; bake 45 minutes more.

title: easy pie
directions: Put pie filling in a baking dish.
Place bread on top of filling.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over bread.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pistachio pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, 1/4 cup nuts and butter in two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake for 15 minutes; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 6 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread over pies. Whip milk with pistachio instant pudding.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread other half of Cool Whip over all.
Garnish with 1/4 cup nuts (can also use cherries).
You can use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: iguana tom's ultimate oven omelette
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 2-quart casserole with Pam or other cooking oil spray.
Gently saute onion and red pepper in 1 tablespoon olive oil until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in corn and remove from heat.
Combine eggs, egg substitute, yogurt and seasonings.
Beat with a wire whisk or hand mixer about 1 minute. Stir in vegetables and pour into casserole.
Bake in upper 1/3 of oven for about 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with Iguana Tom's Ultimate Salsa.

title: granny's corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir.
Bake in a greased pan at 450° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil together 4 cups water, chicken, bay leaves and celery until chicken is done.
Discard bay leaves and celery.
Drain chicken (broth can be used for noodles or dumplings).
Butter casserole dish, cut chicken into bite-size pieces and place in dish.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers and pour melted butter over them and mix.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can serve with rice or potatoes.

title: my elk stew
directions: On a challenge I converted one of my best known recipes for Mediterranean Roll-Ups when we had some rather gamey venison.
This is great with any type of meat that you may have available.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat with an electric mixer for approximately 15 minutes, or mix in a blender for about 7 minutes. This prevents the salad dressing from separating.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.
It keeps indefinitely in the refrigerator.
Excellent over a mixed vegetable salad.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix rest of cookies and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool until firm.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 container Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cookie crust.
Let cool until firm. Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Let cool until firm.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Sprinkle rest of cookie crumbs over top.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is boiled out.
Add applesauce, Equal, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Blend in flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until cake is done.

title: almond chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. May add additional crushed potato chips and shredded cheese on top of casserole halfway through baking time, if desired.

title: never fail fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, butter, milk, fluff and salt. Stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat, being careful not to mistake air bubbles for boiling.

Boil slowly, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes (to soft ball stage) - on a candy thermometer 126° to 240° fudge (240° is better). Remove from heat and stir in chocolate and vanilla until chocolate is melted.
Then, turn into a buttered 9x9-inch pan and cool.

title: oven brown rice
directions: Melt margarine and add rice and soups. Bake 1
hour at 350° in covered dish in oven.

title: zucchini-apricot jam
directions: Place zucchini and sugar in large heavy saucepan; cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil; cook for 15 minutes.
Add pineapple with juice and lemon juice.
Boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; mix with gelatin powder.
Stir well. Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 5 pints.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and then let firm in refrigerator before forming ball.
Chop walnuts for coating.
Roll ball in chopped nuts.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze until solid.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons of ice cream.

title: brown-betty pudding(makes 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1-quart oblong pan.
Stew apples in water until slightly soft.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Mix sugar and spices together.
Arrange 1/3 of apples on bottom of baking pan.
Top apples with 1/3 of bread cubes, then top with 1/3 of butter.
Repeat process 2 more times to make a total of 3 layers.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown in color.
Serve with Hard Sauce.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Cut rhubarb finely. Remove outer (yellow) half of the lemon rinds and slice finely. Mix rhubarb, lemon rind and sugar and let stand overnight. Next day squeeze lemon, strain juice and add juice to mixture. Cook until quite thick, stirring almost constantly to prevent burning. Turn into sterilized jars and seal. Or put in freezer.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and egg.
Add vanilla, then flour, powdered sugar, soda and salt.
Blend in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Frost with a dab of canned sour cream white frosting and top with pecan half.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in 5-quart pot. Add margarine, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until just about done.
Make thicken, of flour and water.
Stir in slowly, then let simmer.
If it gets too thick, add a little more water. Serve with grilled cheese sandwich or bread and butter.
Good on a cold winter day!

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use a teaspoonful and roll like dough.
Then mash like a hamburger.
Put in frying pan and cook until tender.
May be cooked with onion.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello
in
boiling water.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to jello mixture. Turn into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix instant pudding and pineapple together.
Let thicken for about 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Beat well. Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(Can also be baked in two 9-inch round or square layers.)

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: wormie dessert
directions: Prepare pudding as directed.
Crush Oreo cookies; set aside 1/2 package.
In dessert cups, fill 1/3 with Oreo mixture.
Top with pudding for the 2/3 remaining.
Sprinkle with rest of Oreo mixture and gummy worms.
Serves 6.

title: artichoke chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in serving or baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly browned on top. Serve with crackers.
Serves lots.

title: a summer salad
directions: Mix together and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Walnuts are high in polyunsaturated fats.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage leaves just enough to be tender enough to roll. Combine meat, onion, butter, parsley, rice, salt and pepper and 1/3 cup tomato soup. Spread on each leaf. Roll up and fasten with toothpick. Place each roll in a baking pan; pour remaining tomato soup on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: elegant cheese squares
directions: Combine crumbs and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Add butter; mix well. Press firmly with back of spoon over bottom and sides of 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
In a 2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients together.
Cover.
Bake at 350° until done, 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken-vegetable soup
directions: Bring first 8 ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven; cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in chicken and next 5 ingredients. Stir together flour and 1/4 cup water until smooth. Stir into chicken mixture and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer, stirring often, 6 to 8 minutes or until thickened. Yield: 12 cups.

title: rosalie's millionaire pie
directions: Stir lemon juice into milk.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into crust.
Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: ranch dressing
directions: In a medium size
bowl, whisk together the olive oil, vinegar, sugar, marjoram and salt.
Whisk in the yogurt and buttermilk; then stir in the onion, garlic and parsley.
Cover and chill
in the refrigerator for 6 hours or overnight to thicken.

title: cheeseburger skillet dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni to directions on box.
In skillet, brown beef with onion and drain.
Stir in vegetables.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes, then add shredded cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: food for angels
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar slowly until stiff.
Add vanilla. Put crackers in blender, then blend walnuts.
Stir crackers crumbs and walnuts together.
Add this mixture to egg white mixture and blend together with spoon.
Grease and flour oblong pan.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and coconut or sprinkles.
Refrigerate.

title: carolyn's crab dip
directions: Slice onions, including tops.
In heavy Dutch oven, melt cream cheese; add Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add remaining 3 ingredients.
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Serve with crackers or Melba rounds.

title: banana flambe
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Carefully roll them in confectioners sugar and then in flour.
Beat the egg in wide soup dish.
Dip the banana strips in the egg and then into the sugar/flour mix.
Melt butter in large frying pan and cook bananas over medium heat.
Turn them carefully so they don't fall apart. When done, place them gently into a large serving dish.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and then generously pour Grand Marnier over them.
Take dish to the table and light with a match before serving.
Eat immediately.
Serves 6 persons.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes (crisp not soft).
Drain well and add all other ingredients, except crackers.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add Tabasco, 1/2 cup Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese and egg.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine milk and salad oil.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Drop from tablespoon atop bubbling stew.
Cover tightly, bring to a boil, reduce heat and don't lift cover.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: chicken-tater-barbecue
directions: Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic in oil until tender. Add catsup, water, vinegar, sugar and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Arrange chicken parts on top of cut up potatoes in lasagna-type pan.
Pour sauce all over and bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: prime rib
directions: Prime rib at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Roll prime rib in rock salt.
Place on baking rack and pan.
Put in preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake 15 minutes for each pound.
When done, turn off oven and let set for a few minutes before serving.
Cut string and rib will fall off. Slice thickness to your desire.
More doneness on outside end pieces.

title: mother's custard
directions: Separate eggs, putting yolks in a saucepan.
Add sugar, milk, salt and flour.
Stir and cook until mixture comes to a beginning boil.
Remove from stove; add vanilla and let cool.
Whip egg whites until stiff, adding 3 tablespoons of sugar in 3 parts. Fold cool mixture into stiff egg whites.
Cover and put into refrigerator.
Sprinkle with nutmeg when serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apricot angel cake(serves 12)
directions: Bring to a boil the apricot nectar, cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice.
Let cool.
Pour over cake and top with Cool Whip. Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef kushisashi
