directions: Blend soy sauce, green onions, sugar, oil, cornstarch, garlic and ginger in small saucepan.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 1 minute; cool.
Cover and set aside.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch pan, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Pour batter on top.
Add by dropping on batter 2 cups fresh blueberries or your favorite fruit (washed), or 2 cups frozen fruit mixed with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar gradually to butter mixture.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour slowly, beating well on slow speed.
Add vanilla and bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a screw-top jar.
Cover and shake. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pint.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove; set aside.
Spoon off fat.
In skillet, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and broccoli is tender-crisp, stirring often. Garnish with tomato wedges and fresh thyme, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crust:
Cut the butter into flour and, with a wire pastry blender, blend thoroughly.
Press into a 9-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Cool.

title: frozen cheese desserts
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; add sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon onto crust.
Freeze.
Before serving time, let the dessert thaw a little.
Top servings with pie filling.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and set aside for 5 minutes before kneading.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Leave set
for	1/2 hour, then work down.
Leave set an hour or rise
double in bulk and divide in pans, leave set 1/2 hour. Then work down.
Let
set
again 1/2 hour and work down and take a fork, prick each
loaf and let rise double in size. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: broiled zucchini slices
directions: Slice zucchini thin.
Arrange slices on a greased baking sheet.
Spoon margarine on top of each slice.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Place under broiler for about 5 minutes.

title: quick 'n easy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour onto waxed paper in pan.
Chill for several hours.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs, add sugar, melted butter or margarine.
Mix cold water and cornstarch and add to other ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook at 400° for about 10 minutes or until crust has browned.
Turn oven back to 275° or 300°, depending on oven, and cook about 40 more minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: patsy's hearty meat loaf
directions: Make sure fish is scaled good.
Combine corn meal, salt and pepper.
Place on foil in a flat pan or lay flat in a bowl.
Coat fish on both sides with this mixture.
Heat shortening in a large frying pan.
Fry fish until golden brown and flaky on both sides. Remove fish from the pan and drain on a paper towel.
Serve hot with lemon, hot sauce or catsup.

title: j. pat's chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add the rest of ingredients and chili seasoning to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bean casserole
directions: Chop onion into hamburger as it is cooking.
In large pan, mix together sugar, brown sugar, ketchup, dry mustard and vinegar. Add meat.
Add beans.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes uncovered.
Good if made up the night before and let marinate. Can also cook in crock-pot.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: In shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat throughly.
Bake 40 minutes at 450°, stirring occasionally, or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: moist zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, add the ingredients one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour the batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick tests clean.
Let cool a few minutes before removing from pans.

title: presto minestrone
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, saute ground beef, onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water and drain.
Cook onion and pepper in small amount of oil until tender.
Add meat; cook slowly, stirring constantly until meat is crumbly.
Combine meat mixture, macaroni, corn, soup and salt; pour into greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs (bread dressing may be used). Bake for 15 minutes at 375°, or until brown.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and sugar in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn and green beans; place in a buttered casserole dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over casserole.
Melt butter; crush Ritz crackers.
Put cracker crumbs on top and pour melted butter over all.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: french tarts
directions: Pour into unbaked tart shells.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nut and jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into three 8-inch cake pans that have been greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and put filling in between layers and on top of cake.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Set oven for 375° and lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder, soda and salt.
Sift again. Measure sugar with 1/2 cup dry measuring cup.
Place in mixing bowl.
Use same cup to measure brown sugar.
After brown sugar is placed in bowl, measure the shortening and peanut butter.
Break egg into a small bowl.
Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg until well mixed.
Add the dry ingredients that you have measured and stir in until no flour is showing.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of a quarter.
Place the dough balls 3 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Flatten the balls with a fork dipped in flour making a crisscross design by pressing the fork the other way.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven until set but not brown.
Remove from sheet with a spatula and cool on a wire rack. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and beat well.
Pour into fluted unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix both cheeses together well.
Add pecans and salt.
Mix well.
Pinch off parts and form into balls or logs.
Roll in chili powder.
Wrap in clear wrap.
Chill one hour before serving. Spread on crackers.
Great for parties.

title: doc's popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour 1/4 teaspoon salad oil in each cup of popover pan.
Preheat pan to sizzling hot.
Beat all ingredients with rotary beater at full speed until smooth.
Pour batter into pans, filling about 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for additional 20 to 25 minutes.
Popovers are great with gravy.

title: pesto sauce
directions: In food processor, process basil, salt, pepper, garlic and pine nuts.
Add oil as it is processing.
Add cheese until thick but pourable consistency.
Refrigerate 1 week or freeze up to 6 months.

title: zachary's zesty meatballs
directions: Break ground beef into pieces.
Roll into meatballs and brown. Mix jelly and chili sauce in a saucepan and heat up.
When warmed, pour mixture over browned meatballs in a crock-pot and simmer for 2 hours.
Allow 3 hours time:
1 hour for preparation and 2 hours for cooking.

title: jelly donuts
directions: Prepare hot roll mix with 3 tablespoons of the sugar and water.
Let rise, following mix directions.
Turn dough on lightly floured board and knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on lightly floured board or cookie sheet.
Re-roll and cut leftover dough. Cover with clean towel and let rise 30 minutes or until doubled. Fill electric skillet 2/3 full.
Heat to 370°.
Fry donuts, turning once.
Drop into bowl of remaining sugar and coat well. Cut a slit in the side of donut and fill with strawberry preserves, using a large pastry or frosting bag.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine and onion.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and broth and heat until thickens.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with crust.
Bake 30 minutes in 425° oven.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green peppers; drain.
Mix in cream of celery soup and put in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Lay cheese on top of meat mixture.
Arrange Tater Tots on top to cover cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Drain the apricots and pineapple.
Dissolve jello in water. Add mashed or cut up apricots, pineapple and marshmallows to jello when cool.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set, then put on filling followed by cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the onion and squash together for 7 minutes in salted water.
Fold the sour cream, soup and carrots into the drained squash.
Mix the stuffing and melted butter.
Layer half of stuffing mix in casserole, then squash mixture.
Top casserole with rest of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat slightly.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and spread with topping.

title: pistachio squares
directions: Add when mixture is cool, the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Then add pudding mixture and cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.

title: pastry for double crust pie
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly. Gradually add water, tossing with a fork until dough forms a ball. Divide dough in half. Roll out 1/2 to fit 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Transfer to pie plate. Trim even with edges. Fill with desired filling. Roll out second 1/2 and place over filling. Cut slits in top of pastry. Trim to an inch past edge of pie plate. Fold over bottom crust. Flute edges. Bake in oven according to your recipe directions.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and oil to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and drop by spoonful onto waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: shortbread chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups of confectioners sugar.
Beat in vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir in flour until well blended. Stir in chocolate chips.
Dough will be stiff.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork to 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly golden.
Remove to rack.
While cookies are still warm, roll tops in remaining 3 tablespoons of confectioners sugar. Cool.
Makes about 90.

title: mamie eisenhower's million dollar fudge(here is "date bait" that won lieutenant named ike.)
directions: Stir together in a saucepan the sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk. Boil 6 minutes. Place semi-sweet bits, sweet chocolate and marshmallow cream in a large bowl. Pour boiling syrup over chocolate mixture; stir until all chocolate is melted. Stir in nuts. Pour into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan; let stand a few hours before cutting into squares. Store in a tin box.

title: cherry graham pie
directions: Mix margarine and graham cracker crumbs; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Pat crescent rolls in bottom of baking pan and bake as directed.
Chop vegetables.
Mix sour cream, mayo, salad dressing mix together in a bowl and spread over baked crescent rolls. Spread vegetables on top, and cheese on top of vegetables.
Bake for 5 minutes until cheese in melted.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cornbread dressing(serves 20 to 25 people)
directions: Make 4 skillet-size pans cornbread. Saute onions, celery, and bell pepper in margarine. Add cream of chicken soup, red pepper, bouillon cubes (dissolved in liquid), chicken or turkey broth, and boiled eggs together. While mixture is hot, add to crumbled cornbread; mix well. Add green onion tops. Pour into a large baking dish; bake about 40 minutes at 350° or until top gets crusty. Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease
x
x 2-inch baking pan. In large
bowl
combine
flour, sugar, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder,
cloves and salt.
Stir in Country Crock, water and molasses
until well blended.
Pour into pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes
or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly on wire rack.
Serve warm with Lemon Sauce. Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons of cocoa.
Stir in milk, margarine and vanilla.
Pour batter into 9-inch square pan.

title: freezer pickles
directions: In large bowl, combine cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let set for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Pour off water.
Combine vinegar with sugar and both seeds in pan and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and cool.
When cool, drain cucumbers.
Add onion mixture.
Pour syrup over.
Refrigerate covered 2 to 3 days.
Stir once or twice.
Last day, drain slightly and put in Ziploc bags in freezer.

title: smoked turkey breast(cooked on grill)
directions: Mix dressing and soy sauce. Place turkey in plastic bag. Pour sauce over turkey and marinate in refrigerator overnight. Remove turkey from plastic bag, saving liquid. Place turkey in roasting bag. Turn grill on low on one side. Do not turn other side of grill on. Place turkey on cold side of grill. Grill for 5 to 6 hours or 25 minutes per lb.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press crescent roll dough into ungreased 12 x 24-inch pan, forming a rectangle.
Seal the perforations and form a 1 inch crust on sides.
Bake as directed and cool completely.

title: stuffed eggs-sue
directions: Put eggs in a large, heavy pot.
Let come to a rolling boil. Cover pot and boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Turn off fire.
Let sit until cool.
This makes the eggs peel like a dream.
Cut peeled eggs in half and remove yolks.
Add to the yolks the bacon, pickles and salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise to the proper consistency.
Garnish with sliced stuffed olives, caviar or pearl onions.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Then add oats, chips and pecans.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Put asparagus, eggs and sauce in baking dish in layers.
Top with cheese, bread crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together; set aside.
Beat together sugar and margarine.
Add 2 eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with banana and milk.
Mix well after each addition.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: amish fudge candy
directions: Boil white sugar, milk and oleo for 4 minutes.
Have ready the crackers and butterscotch bits.
Add nuts.
Beat well and pour into buttered pan.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in orange sherbet until melted and mix well.
Add oranges and pineapple. Chill until slightly set.
Whip cream and stir into jello mixture. Pour into jello mold.
Set.

title: cherry blossoms
directions: Mix together ingredients for bottom.
Press small amount of mixture (1/2) in bottom of well-greased muffin pans (mixture will raise when baked).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool. Remove from pans.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix dry taco mix, sour cream and cream cheese together. Spread in 9-inch pie plate or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread jar of salsa evenly over top.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, olives and shredded cheese.
Refrigerate until good and cold.
Serve with taco chips.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add vanilla, vinegar, oil and cold water.
Pour batter into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, orange peel, spice and salt in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Place apple slices in unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle sugar mixture over apples.
Dot with butter.
Moisten pastry edge with water; cover with top crust.
Flute edge with fingers or fork.
Cut slits or design in top crust for escape of steam.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: trash
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour half of powdered sugar in bag.
Mix melted chocolate chips and peanut butter with cereal.
Pour in bag.
Top with remaining sugar.
Shake and serve.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Remove sausage from casings and break into pieces. Saute onion in oil and add sausage. Fry until tender and browned.
Add remainder of ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender. Serve with rolls and butter.

title: crumbs for pies
directions: Makes enough for 2 pies.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Cook chicken in water until done.
Set resulting chicken broth aside; bone chicken
when cool.
In the 2-quart pot, brown sausage (sliced) in oil.
Set sausage aside.
Add flour to oil, stirring, over low heat until dark golden brown.
Stir in ham, green pepper, celery and onions.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until vegetables soften.
Add the reserved broth, stirring until smooth; add the seasoning.
Add the chicken and sausage.
Simmer, stirring occasionally.
Before serving, stir in green onions.
Serve over rice in bowls.

title: lemon or lime fluff
directions: Chill milk overnight; dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and lemon or lime juice.
Let stand until syrupy.
Whip milk until stiff.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar; fold in Jell-O mixture.
When mixture has thickened, pour in graham cracker crust.

title: punch for 100
directions: Melt sugar in hot water. Heat but do not boil. Add jello and Kool-Aid.
Cool. Add orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice and apple juice.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Wash pork chops and place in shallow pan.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Place onions on top of pork chops, then place tomato slices on top of onions.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scottish scones
directions: Mix dry ingredients and butter (or bacon fat) until crumbly. Add beaten egg and enough buttermilk to make gooey biscuit dough. Pat 1/2-inch thick on well floured board; cut with knife or biscuit cutter.
Cook on low on heated griddle; turn when slightly browned.
Or bake on cookie sheet at 350° until light brown. Clean pan between bakings.

title: vanilla pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Mix baking powder and crushed vanilla wafers.
Add vanilla wafer mixture to creamed butter and sugar. Add a little at a time.
Also, add one egg at a time, beating after each egg.
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine cinnamon and sugar; cut biscuits into fourths and roll in cinnamon mixture.
Press biscuits into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt butter;
add brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza(children's)
directions: Unroll dough and press over bottom and side of 12-inch pizza pan to make crust.
Sprinkle sausage, potatoes and cheese over dough.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl.
Beat with fork until mixed up.
Pour over pizza dough very carefully.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring the sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa to a boil; do not overcook.
Remove and add the vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Stir 4 minutes and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet to cool.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Drop raisins in boiling water for 1 minute to soften, then cool.
Cut all stems off heads of broccoli.
Combine celery and raw broccoli flowerets with mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, pecans, Parmesan cheese, onion, raisins and bacon pieces.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: cheese-garlic bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Slice French bread and spread on generously.
Toast. Can be frozen.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Layer corn in bottom of dish.
Mix other ingredients and spread over corn.
Crumble 1 stack of Ritz crackers and mix with 1 stick of melted margarine and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into walnut-sized balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Just thaw and warm to serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in small chunks; dice eggs.
Mix with remaining ingredients very well.
Season to taste with black pepper and Accent, garlic powder or garlic salt.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley and sliced boiled egg.
Sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pie crust.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with rotary beater.
Stir in black walnuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill. Roll into balls (walnut size).
Freeze.
While still frozen, place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 75.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook
first
three
ingredients
until thick and brown. The browner
it is cooked, the more butterscotch taste it has. Mix last
three
ingredients
together;
mix
well.
Stir into first mixture stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Slightly cool and pour into baked pie crust.

title: burgers
directions: Brown meat and seasoning in skillet.
Drain grease from meat. Add onions, sweet relish, prepared mustard and mayonnaise.
Remove from heat immediately and serve on hamburger buns.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together; do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: oreo dream
directions: Crumble the cookies in a food chopper or blender. Melt the butter and

mix with the crumbs. Press 1/2 of the crumbs into a 13 x 9 pan, reserving 1/2 crumbs for topping. Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over crumbs. Chill in freezer. Prepare chocolate pudding using only 2 3/4 cups milk instead of 3. Spread pudding over the cream cheese layer and chill again. Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle crumbs on top.

title: canton chicken wings
directions: Wipe chicken wings with a damp cloth; pat dry.
Cut them through the joints into three pieces each; discard the wing tips or use them to make stock.
Heat oil in a skillet or wok; saute the chicken pieces until nicely browned on both sides, about 4 or 5 minutes.
Blend soy sauce, sherry, vinegar and honey.
Add with all other ingredients to the skillet.
Cover tightly and simmer gently for about half an hour or until chicken is tender.
Stir a few times while cooking.
Put chicken on a platter; coat with the sauce and serve.
Serves 4 to 6 persons.

title: frosted chocolate(usa)
directions: Add chocolate syrup to chilled milk, beat with rotary beater and add ice cream.

title: mom's hungarian goulash with egg noodles(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven; drain and crumble bacon and set aside. Saute chopped onion in bacon drippings; drain on paper towels. Brown meat cut up into 1-inch cubes in grease and drain excess off. Add wine, water, ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire and vinegar over meat into the pot; then add spices of dry mustard, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat 2 to 2 1/2 hours or cook in crock-pot 8 hours.
Fifteen to twenty minutes before serving, boil the noodles in another pot; drain and save. Add 1/2 cup sour cream (or more if desired).
Serve in 2 bowls. Sprinkle poppy seed over noodles with melted butter (optional); combine on plates as served and toss to coat.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Cut shortening into flour mixture with blender or fork until the mixture looks like coarse cornmeal.
Stir in grated cheese.
Add milk to shortening-flour mixture and mix just enough to hold dough together.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and bake on ungreased cookie sheet, in hot oven (425°) for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown as desired.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Cook onion and bacon, and place in a serving bowl. Slice the cooked potato and layer over the top. Add vinegar, salt and pepper, mix thoroughly. Add oil slowly you may not need as much. Taste, you may like to add more vinegar. Garnish ans serve.

title: root beer
directions: Mix sugar and extract.
Dissolve 1/2 cake yeast in small amount of water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add 1 gallon of lukewarm water and mix very well.
Store in a dark, cool place for 24 hours or longer.

title: grape salad
directions: Separate and rinse grapes.
Cream remaining ingredients together, and gently toss grapes with cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate.

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt oleo over medium heat and saute onions until clear and tender.
Butter a 2-quart, 8 x 11 x 2-inch casserole.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of crackers for topping.
Line dish with remaining crumbs.
Add onions and soup in alternate layers.
Cover top with beaten eggs and pour cheese and crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: pound cake
directions: Measure all ingredients and put in one bowl before starting mixer.
Beat 10 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In an electric skillet, brown chicken slowly in oil.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sherry, mushrooms, bay leaf and garlic.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Uncover, add drained onions and ripe olives.
Simmer rapidly until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: shrimp noel
directions: Cook mushrooms in 1/4 cup margarine until tender.
Combine shrimp, rice, vegetables and seasonings.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
It can be garnished with parsley and sliced olives.
Serves 4.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Saute onion, pepper and celery. Mix these ingredients.
Cook noodles by package directions. Microwave diced cheese, mushrooms, 1/2 cup milk and mushroom soup until cheese melts.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Melt fat; cook onion.
Put in meat, rice, celery and beans. Combine seasonings and soup and pour over meat mixture.
Cook 2 hours very slowly in covered skillet.

title: joe's venison roast
directions: Coat roast with mustard and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Before cooking, scrape off all the mustard possible; do not wash.
Place roast, potatoes, carrots, onions, salt and pepper to taste, diced garlic and 1/2 cup of water in oven cooking bag and cook according to oven bag directions or as any other roast.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Mix well and chill. Serve over mixed salad greens.

title: raspberry marble cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat spring-form pan with cooking spray.
In a food processor, combine Cheerios, vanilla wafers and sugar.
Process until fine crumbs form.
Add oil and water; process until evenly moistened.
Press mixture on bottom and up sides of pan.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Place sliced apples in 2-quart casserole (buttered).
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add cheese and flour.
Spread cream mixture on top of apples.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, cheese, chilies, olives, green onion and garlic.
Spread evenly on 5 (10-inch) tortillas.
Roll up; refrigerate for few hours.
Slice in 1/4 inch slices and arrange on plate; garnish with fresh parsley.
Serve with salsa.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mock chow mein casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in covered casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together and pour in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Cover with topping; bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chip and vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: rotini
directions: Must prepare night before.
Cook whole box rotini.
While rotini is cooking, use an electric mixer to mix Hellmann's, water, sugar, vinegar and turmeric.
Drain rotini and add hot rotini to mixture; add celery and onion and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in baking dish; cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: pineapple barbecue sauce chili dogs
directions: Simmer to blend ingredients.
Add 1 large can drained pineapple chunks.
Pour over hot dogs and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix together and blow bubbles!

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Gradually mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses, beating after each addition. Beat until fluffy. Add flour, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Roll into small balls, then roll into sugar. Bake for 11 to 12 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt
margarine.
Combine
flour,
sugar and milk.
Put the melted
margarine
in
a
long Pyrex dish and add peaches. Add flour, sugar and milk mixture on top of the peaches.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: asparagus and sauce
directions: Cook asparagus on low heat until almost tender; drain.
Chop chicken livers and saute in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Blend sauteed-chopped chicken livers with mayonnaise and onion to make a sauce.
Arrange asparagus on broiler pan; top with sauce.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Brown in broiler 3 inches from heat.

title: mamma's cottage pudding
directions: Sift flour once and measure the 2 cups; add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream together with milk.

Add flour, alternating with the milk, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth. Add vanilla and bake in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in a moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix butter and cheese. Add flour gradually.
When well mixed, add red pepper.
Fill cookie press, using star disk.
Form straws on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: About 3 dozen.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in sugar, crackers, nuts and vanilla. Bake in buttered pie dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with ice cream, whipped cream, or plain.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Grilled Flank Steak is a recipe that was printed in either the Family Circle or Today's Woman back in the late 1950's.
At that time, you could buy the steak for forty-nine cents a pound.
About three weeks after this recipe appeared, the price was seventy-five cents a pound.

title: migas
directions: In a nonstick pan, melt margarine and add corn tortillas, torn or cut into small pieces.
Saute and then add eggs and salt and scramble until cooked.
Top with shredded cheese and serve.
Great for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Melt cheese and soup in double boiler.
Add gelatin.
Cool for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in oiled mold. Refrigerate until set.

title: fruity yellow cake
directions: Pour pie filling into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, then pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over top and dot with butter, then pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°, start checking after 45 minutes.
Done when brown on top.

title: coconut carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) square cake pans.
On sheet of waxed paper, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In large bowl, at high speed, beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla until blended.
At low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture; at medium speed, beat until blended.
Stir in carrots, pineapple, coconut, chopped pecans and raisins.
Pour batter into prepared pans, dividing evenly.
Bake for 30 minutes until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool layers in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack and cool completely.

title: bacardi punch
directions: About 1 hour before serving time, squeeze 4 oranges and 2 lemons into a glass pitcher or bowl.
Add pineapple juice and sweeten to taste.
Add Bacardi.
Slice remaining orange and lemon thin, then cut into small triangular pieces.
Stir well.
Cover. Let stand until serving time.
Just before serving, place block of ice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale to juice mixture and pour over ice.
Garnish with orange and lemon slices.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients and boil on top of stove, often stirring for one minute (no more, no less).
Blend last three ingredients into cocoa mixture.
After mixing, drop onto wax paper and let stand until hardened.
